2026-01-07 23:33:58.451009+00	2026-01-07 23:33:58.45102+00	6b5d9899-7210-420e-858e-8f5257b22160	\N	1	{"content": "<h3 class=\\"font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\\">Reef Briefing  Visitor Code of Conduct  Eco-Pledge Agreement</h3>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">Welcome to the Parque Nacional Arrecife de Puerto Morelos, part of the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef System  the second-largest coral reef in the world. This is a protected national marine park, and your actions directly impact its health.</p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">Before entering the water, please read and agree to the following rules. This is both a legal requirement and part of our eco-commitment as licensed guides and operators.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 class=\\"font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\\">What Makes This Place Special?</h3>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">Protected as a National Park since 1998, managed by CONANP (National Commission of Protected Natural Areas)</p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">Home to 500+ species of fish, 60+ species of coral, and multiple endangered marine species</p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">Critical habitat for sea turtles, reef fish, corals, crustaceans, and juvenile species</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">Entry into the marine park requires:</p>\\r\\n<ol class=\\"list-decimal ml-6 space-y-2\\">\\r\\n  <li>A licensed guide</li>\\r\\n  <li>A valid marine park admission bracelet</li>\\r\\n  <li>Your acknowledgment and agreement to follow park rules</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 class=\\"font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\\">What You MUST Do</h3>\\r\\n<ol class=\\"list-decimal ml-6 space-y-2\\">\\r\\n  <li>Maintain at least 2 meters (6 feet) of distance from all corals, including soft corals.</li>\\r\\n  <li>Control your buoyancy  stay neutrally buoyant before approaching the reef</li>\\r\\n  <li>Stay off the bottom  do not kneel, sit, or stand on sand, coral rubble, seagrass, or rocks</li>\\r\\n  <li>Keep your fins level with or above your body at all times near the reef</li>\\r\\n  <li>Avoid vertical or \\"fins-down\\" posture  remain horizontal for safety and control</li>\\r\\n  <li>Follow your guide and stay within the designated dive/snorkel area</li>\\r\\n  <li>Secure all loose gear  hoses, gauges, clips, cameras, DSMB, slates, wetnotes, etc..</li>\\r\\n  <li>Rinse off all sunscreen and body products before entering the water</li>\\r\\n  <li>Wear your park admission bracelet visibly throughout the activity</li>\\r\\n  <li>Ask questions if you're unsure  we're here to help</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 class=\\"font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\\">What You MUST NOT Do</h3>\\r\\n<ol class=\\"list-decimal ml-6 space-y-2\\">\\r\\n  <li>Do not touch any organisms, living or dead.</li>\\r\\n  <li>Do not kick, kneel, stand on, hold, or lean on coral, rocks, seagrass, or the seafloor. Even sand contains living organisms. There is also risk of injury from stingrays, moray eels, scorpionfish, jellies, fire coral, and hydroids with stinging cells that are hiding out of sight! Protect the reef and yourself!</li>\\r\\n  <li>Do not wear sunscreen, even if labeled reef-safe  use rash guards, or hats instead</li>\\r\\n  <li>No gloves,, knives, reef hooks, pointers, probes, dive sticks, etc..  bare hands only, no exceptions</li>\\r\\n  <li>Do not chase, corner, harass, or feed marine life</li>\\r\\n  <li>Do not collect shells, coral, sand, or any marine material, dead or alive.</li>\\r\\n  <li>Do not allow cameras or gear to dangle or drag where they can strike coral or marine life, tuck your SPG and Octo. All hoses, gauges, DSMB's,slates, wetnotes, etc, should be streamlined and kept close to your body away from any possible contact.</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 class=\\"font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\\">Underwater Photography Reminders</h3>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">Be a diver first, photographer second.</p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">Never rest or hold on to the reef or get too close to marine life for a photo. You MUST remain 2 meters away from any corals. The park rules make no exceptions for your photographic shots.</p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">If you are still mastering buoyancy and are not 100% certain you can maintain control, task load, manage your gas consumption, or be fully mindful of your situational awareness, leave the camera behind and enjoy the dive your gas will last longer!</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 class=\\"font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\\">What Happens If I Break the Rules in the National Park?</h3>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">We may have to end the dive prematurely.</p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">If you have concerns about your own diving skills and maybe want extra practice talk to us we will make a diving plan to help you gain skills and confidence for diving on the reef in more sensitive areas in the national park.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 class=\\"font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\\">Why is my guide being so strict?</h3>\\r\\n<ol class=\\"list-decimal ml-6 space-y-2\\">\\r\\n  <li>Guides are official partners of CONANP and act as park stewards.</li>\\r\\n  <li>Your guide's role is not just to show you the reef as a role model  but to protect it.</li>\\r\\n  <li>Following these rules ensures your safety, and the reef's survival for future generations.</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 class=\\"font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\\">Why This Matters</h3>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">Even a single fin kick, accidental touch, or kicked-up cloud of sand can damage coral that took decades to grow, and stop baby coral polyps you can't even see from propagating.</p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">If you touch it you kill it.</p>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">This reef is home to:</p>\\r\\n<ol class=\\"list-decimal ml-6 space-y-2\\">\\r\\n  <li>Sea turtles</li>\\r\\n  <li>Endangered corals (staghorn, elkhorn)</li>\\r\\n  <li>Nursery fish</li>\\r\\n  <li>Queen conch</li>\\r\\n  <li>Caribbean lobster</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n<p class=\\"mb-4\\">Your awareness and actions directly protect this living ecosystem. If in doubt, maintain distance.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3 class=\\"font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\\">Before Entering the Water:</h3>\\r\\n<ol class=\\"list-decimal ml-6 space-y-2\\">\\r\\n  <li>Rinse off lotions, sunscreen, and oils</li>\\r\\n  <li>Tuck in all gear  no dangling hoses, clips, DSMB's, Slates, cameras, or other dangly do's</li>\\r\\n  <li>Check your weights, trim, and buoyancy</li>\\r\\n  <li>Ask for a refresher or buoyancy check if it's been a while.</li>\\r\\n  <li>When in doubt  ask! There are no dumb questions!</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<div class=\\"mt-8 pt-4 border-t space-y-6\\">\\r\\n  <div class=\\"no-print bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded p-4\\">\\r\\n    <p class=\\"text-sm text-blue-800 mb-2\\">Please review this document carefully before signing.</p>\\r\\n    <button type=\\"button\\" onclick=\\"window.print()\\" class=\\"px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 text-sm\\">\\r\\n      Print Document for Review\\r\\n    </button>\\r\\n  </div>\\r\\n  <div>\\r\\n    <h4 class=\\"font-semibold mb-3\\">Eco-Pledge & Acknowledgment</h4>\\r\\n    <div class=\\"space-y-2\\">\\r\\n      <label class=\\"flex items-start gap-2\\">\\r\\n        <input type=\\"checkbox\\" name=\\"eco_pledge\\" class=\\"mt-1\\">\\r\\n        <span>By signing below, I confirm that I have read, understood, and agree to follow all national park rules and responsible diving practices as outlined above. I understand that my participation is subject to these terms and that violations result in immediate ejection from the national park without refund.</span>\\r\\n      </label>\\r\\n    </div>\\r\\n    <div class=\\"print-only\\">\\r\\n      <p class=\\"mb-4\\"><strong>Name of Diver/Snorkeler:</strong> John Diver</p>\\r\\n      <p class=\\"mb-4\\"><strong>Signature:</strong> _______________________</p>\\r\\n      <p><strong>Date:</strong> 2026-01-07</p>\\r\\n    </div>\\r\\n  </div>\\r\\n  <div class=\\"no-print bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded p-4\\">\\r\\n    <p class=\\"text-sm text-blue-800 mb-2\\">Before signing electronically, you may print a copy for review.</p>\\r\\n    <button type=\\"button\\" onclick=\\"window.print()\\" class=\\"px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 text-sm\\">\\r\\n      Print for Review\\r\\n    </button>\\r\\n  </div>\\r\\n</div>", "signed_ip": "127.0.0.1", "content_hash": "fdf8ef75de434136d5cd443269d4e7315940275f4446abc844fbd0256f4f8587", "template_name": "Dive Briefing: Parque Nacional Arrecife de Puerto Morelos", "signed_by_name": "john diver", "template_version": "1.0"}	Initial agreement	081ecc64-ec60-4e49-8ee9-d24059d1b57d	1
