2026-01-09 16:38:29.11898+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.118999+00	6f8ab970-3308-405b-a394-8d97c9681a16	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Staff accounts provide access to the dive operations dashboard based on assigned roles.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Account Access</h3>\\n<p>Your account provides access based on your staff permissions. The system tracks all actions in the audit log for accountability.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Profile Link</h3>\\n<p>Click <strong>Profile</strong> in the sidebar to access your personal settings. Click <strong>Log out</strong> to end your session.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Session Security</h3>\\n<p>Sessions expire after a period of inactivity. For security, always log out when using shared computers.</p>"}	0	t	c48df9be-c104-432a-be07-f8ceeb7c2888
2026-01-09 16:38:29.128135+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.128153+00	d71691a8-2e73-49e9-b027-e291c1c25ffd	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Diver profiles (DiverProfile model) store comprehensive information about each diver including contact details, certifications, medical status, and equipment sizing.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Creating a New Diver</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Navigate to <strong>Divers</strong> in the sidebar</li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Add Diver</strong></li>\\n    <li>Complete the form sections described below</li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Create Diver</strong></li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Personal Information (Required)</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>First Name</strong> - Diver's first name</li>\\n    <li><strong>Last Name</strong> - Diver's last name</li>\\n    <li><strong>Email</strong> - Primary contact email</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Certification Section</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Agency</strong> - Certification agency (PADI, SSI, NAUI, etc.)</li>\\n    <li><strong>Level</strong> - Certification level (Open Water, Advanced, Rescue, Divemaster, etc.)</li>\\n    <li><strong>Certification Number</strong> - Card number for verification</li>\\n    <li><strong>Certification Date</strong> - Date certification was issued</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Experience</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Total Dives</strong> - Logged dive count for experience tracking</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Medical Clearance</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Clearance Date</strong> - When physician clearance was obtained</li>\\n    <li><strong>Valid Until</strong> - Expiration date of medical clearance</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Diver Profile</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Diver Type</strong>:\\n        <ul>\\n            <li><em>Does Diving (Activity)</em> - Diving is an activity they do</li>\\n            <li><em>Diver (Identity)</em> - Diving is core to their identity</li>\\n        </ul>\\n    </li>\\n    <li><strong>Equipment Ownership</strong>:\\n        <ul>\\n            <li><em>None - Rents All</em> - Full rental customer</li>\\n            <li><em>Partial - Owns Some Gear</em> - Hybrid rental</li>\\n            <li><em>Full - Owns All Essential Gear</em> - Brings own equipment</li>\\n        </ul>\\n    </li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Body Measurements</h3>\\n<p>Used for equipment fitting and weighting calculations:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Weight (kg)</strong> - For buoyancy calculations</li>\\n    <li><strong>Height (cm)</strong> - For wetsuit sizing</li>\\n    <li><strong>Weight Required (kg)</strong> - Calculated neutral buoyancy weight</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Gear Sizes</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Wetsuit Size</strong> - e.g., M, L, XL</li>\\n    <li><strong>BCD Size</strong> - e.g., M, L, XL</li>\\n    <li><strong>Fin Size</strong> - e.g., M/L, 9-10</li>\\n    <li><strong>Mask Fit</strong> - e.g., Low volume, Standard</li>\\n    <li><strong>Glove Size</strong> - e.g., M, L, XL</li>\\n    <li><strong>Gear Notes</strong> - Additional preferences or requirements</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	ce7a9db3-02da-4867-a778-001d7aa76775
2026-01-11 00:09:10.86604+00	2026-01-11 00:09:10.866055+00	c2e6cd9f-ae70-40cc-87ac-775dca5d5fa4	\N	rich_text	{"body": "\\n<h2>Understanding Message Profiles</h2>\\n<p>Message Profiles define the sender identity for your outbound communications. They control the \\"From\\" name, email address, and reply-to settings for different languages (English and Spanish).</p>\\n\\n<h3>Why Use Message Profiles?</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Brand Consistency:</strong> Ensure all emails come from recognizable sender identities</li>\\n    <li><strong>Multi-language Support:</strong> Different sender addresses for English and Spanish communications</li>\\n    <li><strong>Reply Management:</strong> Route replies to the appropriate team or mailbox</li>\\n    <li><strong>AWS SES Configuration:</strong> Track deliverability with different configuration sets</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Accessing Message Profiles</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Navigate to the Staff Portal</li>\\n    <li>Go to <strong>System &gt; Message Profiles</strong></li>\\n    <li>View all configured sender profiles</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Creating a New Profile</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Add Profile</strong></li>\\n    <li>Fill in the required fields:</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h4>Basic Information</h4>\\n<table>\\n    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th><th>Example</th></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Name</td><td>Display name for the profile</td><td>Transactional Emails</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Slug</td><td>Unique identifier (auto-generated)</td><td>transactional-emails</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>From Name</td><td>Sender name shown in email clients</td><td>Happy Diving MX</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Active</td><td>Whether this profile can be used</td><td>Yes</td></tr>\\n</table>\\n\\n<h4>English Identity</h4>\\n<table>\\n    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th><th>Example</th></tr>\\n    <tr><td>From Address (EN)</td><td>Email address for English messages</td><td>bookings@happydiving.mx</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Reply-To (EN)</td><td>Where English replies go (optional)</td><td>support@happydiving.mx</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>SES Config Set (EN)</td><td>AWS SES configuration set name</td><td>happydiving-transactional</td></tr>\\n</table>\\n\\n<h4>Spanish Identity</h4>\\n<table>\\n    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th><th>Example</th></tr>\\n    <tr><td>From Address (ES)</td><td>Email address for Spanish messages</td><td>reservas@buceofeliz.com</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Reply-To (ES)</td><td>Where Spanish replies go (optional)</td><td>soporte@buceofeliz.com</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>SES Config Set (ES)</td><td>AWS SES configuration set name</td><td>buceofeliz-transactional</td></tr>\\n</table>\\n\\n<h3>Setting a Default Profile</h3>\\n<p>One profile can be designated as the default for all outgoing messages:</p>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Go to the profile detail page</li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Set as Default</strong></li>\\n    <li>This profile will be used when no specific profile is specified</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>How Profiles Are Used</h3>\\n<p>When sending a message, the system:</p>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Determines the recipient's language preference (locale)</li>\\n    <li>Selects the appropriate sender identity (EN or ES) from the profile</li>\\n    <li>Sets the From address and Reply-To header accordingly</li>\\n    <li>Uses the configured SES settings for delivery tracking</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Best Practices</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Verify all email addresses</strong> in AWS SES before using them</li>\\n    <li><strong>Use descriptive names</strong> for profiles (e.g., \\"Marketing\\", \\"Transactional\\", \\"Support\\")</li>\\n    <li><strong>Set up reply-to addresses</strong> that are actively monitored</li>\\n    <li><strong>Configure SES configuration sets</strong> for delivery tracking and bounce handling</li>\\n    <li><strong>Keep one default profile</strong> for general communications</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Common Profile Types</h3>\\n<table>\\n    <tr><th>Profile Type</th><th>Use Case</th><th>Example From Name</th></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Transactional</td><td>Booking confirmations, receipts</td><td>Happy Diving Bookings</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Marketing</td><td>Newsletters, promotions</td><td>Happy Diving MX</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Support</td><td>Customer service replies</td><td>Happy Diving Support</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>No-Reply</td><td>Automated notifications</td><td>Happy Diving (No Reply)</td></tr>\\n</table>\\n"}	0	t	5479817f-cd3b-4441-b86b-aa9a02088030
2026-01-11 00:09:55.548635+00	2026-01-11 00:09:55.548653+00	3c1a3f3c-26be-40d9-ba1a-118bfbd080b8	\N	rich_text	{"body": "\\n<h2>Understanding Message Templates</h2>\\n<p>Message Templates are pre-configured email and SMS messages that can be sent to customers. Each template has a unique key used by the system to identify it when sending automated messages.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Accessing Message Templates</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Navigate to the Staff Portal</li>\\n    <li>Go to <strong>System &gt; Message Templates</strong></li>\\n    <li>View all configured templates</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Creating a New Template</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Add Template</strong></li>\\n    <li>Fill in the required fields:</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h4>Basic Information</h4>\\n<table>\\n    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th><th>Example</th></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Template Key</td><td>Unique identifier used in code (cannot change after creation)</td><td>booking_confirmation</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Display Name</td><td>Human-readable name</td><td>Booking Confirmation</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Message Type</td><td>Determines default routing (transactional = email, reminder = SMS)</td><td>transactional</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Description</td><td>Brief description of when this template is used</td><td>Sent after booking is confirmed</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Active</td><td>Whether this template can be used</td><td>Yes</td></tr>\\n</table>\\n\\n<h3>Using Template Variables</h3>\\n<p>Templates support Django template syntax for dynamic content. Wrap variable names in double curly braces:</p>\\n\\n<h4>Recipient Variables</h4>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><code>{{ recipient.first_name }}</code> - Recipient's first name</li>\\n    <li><code>{{ recipient.last_name }}</code> - Recipient's last name</li>\\n    <li><code>{{ recipient.email }}</code> - Recipient's email address</li>\\n    <li><code>{{ recipient.phone }}</code> - Recipient's phone number</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h4>Custom Context Variables</h4>\\n<p>Any custom data passed to the template is available. Common examples:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><code>{{ booking.reference }}</code> - Booking reference number</li>\\n    <li><code>{{ booking.date }}</code> - Booking date</li>\\n    <li><code>{{ excursion.name }}</code> - Excursion name</li>\\n    <li><code>{{ payment.amount }}</code> - Payment amount</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Email Content</h3>\\n<table>\\n    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Subject Line</td><td>Email subject, supports template variables</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Plain Text Body</td><td>Text version of the email (required for accessibility)</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>HTML Body</td><td>Styled HTML version (optional but recommended)</td></tr>\\n</table>\\n\\n<h4>HTML Email Best Practices</h4>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Use inline CSS styles (not external stylesheets)</li>\\n    <li>Keep width under 600px for mobile compatibility</li>\\n    <li>Include both HTML and plain text versions</li>\\n    <li>Test in multiple email clients (Gmail, Outlook, etc.)</li>\\n    <li>Use web-safe fonts (Arial, Helvetica, Georgia)</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>SMS Content</h3>\\n<table>\\n    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr>\\n    <tr><td>SMS Message</td><td>Text message content (keep under 160 characters for single SMS)</td></tr>\\n</table>\\n\\n<h4>SMS Best Practices</h4>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Keep messages under 160 characters when possible</li>\\n    <li>Include essential information only</li>\\n    <li>Add business name for recognition</li>\\n    <li>Avoid special characters that may not display</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Previewing Templates</h3>\\n<p>From the template detail page:</p>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Open in New Tab</strong> to see rendered HTML</li>\\n    <li>Use <strong>Toggle Size</strong> to preview desktop vs mobile widths</li>\\n    <li>Review the inline preview with sample data</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Template Types</h3>\\n<table>\\n    <tr><th>Type</th><th>Default Channel</th><th>Use Case</th></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Transactional</td><td>Email</td><td>Confirmations, receipts, important updates</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Reminder</td><td>SMS</td><td>Appointment reminders, day-before notifications</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Marketing</td><td>Email</td><td>Newsletters, promotions (requires consent)</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>Alert</td><td>Both</td><td>Urgent notifications, cancellations</td></tr>\\n</table>\\n\\n<h3>Common Templates</h3>\\n<table>\\n    <tr><th>Template Key</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>\\n    <tr><td>booking_confirmation</td><td>Sent after booking is confirmed</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>booking_reminder_24h</td><td>Reminder 24 hours before excursion</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>booking_cancelled</td><td>Cancellation notification</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>welcome_diver</td><td>Welcome email for new divers</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>payment_receipt</td><td>Payment confirmation</td></tr>\\n    <tr><td>medical_form_request</td><td>Request to complete medical form</td></tr>\\n</table>\\n"}	0	t	87bd91eb-fc65-4629-95ce-0d5762079caf
2026-01-11 11:05:38.93675+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.93676+00	f2be3915-2bc2-445e-b76e-920d7c13ed33	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Cozumel, Mexico, is consistently ranked among the world's top dive destinations, and for good reason. With crystal-clear waters, dramatic wall dives, and an incredible variety of marine life, this Caribbean island offers something for divers of every skill level.</p>"}	0	t	5555f629-cd77-4519-a09a-fc32c1739d1e
2026-01-11 11:05:38.9392+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.939209+00	7a079ef3-e646-4c66-8c7a-8dad8267e857	\N	heading	{"text": "1. Palancar Reef", "level": 2}	1	t	5555f629-cd77-4519-a09a-fc32c1739d1e
2026-01-11 11:05:38.941632+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.941641+00	075e47b4-7a21-421c-9a5f-a6e9e97892f8	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Perhaps the most famous dive site in Cozumel, Palancar Reef is actually a series of dive sites along a massive reef system. The towering coral formations, swim-throughs, and abundant marine life make this a must-dive destination. Look for eagle rays, sea turtles, and the occasional nurse shark.</p>"}	2	t	5555f629-cd77-4519-a09a-fc32c1739d1e
2026-01-11 11:05:38.943754+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.943764+00	edf86960-8534-4ab5-8371-281ed5a5384e	\N	heading	{"text": "2. Santa Rosa Wall", "level": 2}	3	t	5555f629-cd77-4519-a09a-fc32c1739d1e
2026-01-11 11:05:38.946046+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.946062+00	192656cb-f381-445f-88ee-3e740c412df0	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>For experienced divers, Santa Rosa Wall offers one of the most exhilarating drift dives in the Caribbean. The wall drops from 50 feet to well beyond recreational limits, featuring massive sponges, black coral, and deep overhangs perfect for exploring.</p>"}	4	t	5555f629-cd77-4519-a09a-fc32c1739d1e
