2026-01-11 11:05:38.95127+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.951285+00	8322bdf3-243e-4d1d-b0c0-4cb1490fe57e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Home to some of the largest coral pinnacles in Cozumel, Columbia Deep is where you'll find stunning formations rising from 80-100 feet. The area is known for encounters with spotted eagle rays and large groupers.</p>"}	6	t	5555f629-cd77-4519-a09a-fc32c1739d1e
2026-01-11 11:05:38.953759+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.95377+00	736179d2-9a42-4be2-93bf-47286ea37a76	\N	call_to_action	{"text": "Book your Cozumel diving adventure with us today!", "title": "Ready to Dive Cozumel?", "button_url": "/excursions/", "button_text": "View Excursions"}	7	t	5555f629-cd77-4519-a09a-fc32c1739d1e
2026-01-11 11:05:38.963461+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.963472+00	58f27b8c-247d-4b2a-9530-8fbd6c33b17b	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>A wetsuit is one of the most important pieces of diving equipment you'll own. It keeps you warm, protects you from stings and scrapes, and can even add buoyancy. But with so many options available, how do you choose the right one?</p>"}	0	t	5375ce84-24dc-4a33-a2a9-0de89157fb0a
2026-01-11 11:05:38.965473+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.965491+00	55836240-9dcd-4949-a29f-669af8280499	\N	heading	{"text": "Understanding Wetsuit Thickness", "level": 2}	1	t	5375ce84-24dc-4a33-a2a9-0de89157fb0a
2026-01-11 11:05:38.96757+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.96758+00	781b4972-702d-4e72-bc44-a675ba6c6a4b	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<ul><li><strong>3mm</strong> - Warm tropical waters (80F/27C and above)</li><li><strong>5mm</strong> - Temperate waters (68-80F/20-27C)</li><li><strong>7mm</strong> - Cold water diving (50-68F/10-20C)</li><li><strong>Semi-dry or Drysuit</strong> - Very cold water (below 50F/10C)</li></ul>"}	2	t	5375ce84-24dc-4a33-a2a9-0de89157fb0a
2026-01-11 11:05:38.970086+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.970094+00	45867be5-f8f3-43dd-a6ae-1471421d0cd9	\N	heading	{"text": "Getting the Right Fit", "level": 2}	3	t	5375ce84-24dc-4a33-a2a9-0de89157fb0a
2026-01-11 11:05:38.972075+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.972081+00	862d8a84-a66b-4384-aced-90e6e23a7447	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>A properly fitting wetsuit should be snug but not restrictive. Water should not flow freely through the suit, but you should still be able to move and breathe comfortably. Here are key fit points to check:</p><ul><li>No gaps at the neck, wrists, or ankles</li><li>Smooth contact across the back with no air pockets</li><li>Full range of motion in arms and legs</li><li>Comfortable when bending at waist and knees</li></ul>"}	4	t	5375ce84-24dc-4a33-a2a9-0de89157fb0a
2026-01-11 11:05:38.979968+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.979984+00	4f36063c-a3ae-4695-9a03-68d201693cac	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Getting your Open Water certification is your ticket to exploring the underwater world. This certification allows you to dive independently with a buddy to depths of 18 meters (60 feet) anywhere in the world. Here's everything you need to know about the process.</p>"}	0	t	a1ab91bc-f123-44ec-9004-e74c6c92d9cc
2026-01-11 11:05:38.983444+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.983464+00	77a0e756-fb68-4c7f-9e60-91ad5ec0b620	\N	heading	{"text": "Choosing a Certification Agency", "level": 2}	1	t	a1ab91bc-f123-44ec-9004-e74c6c92d9cc
2026-01-11 11:05:38.987037+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.987054+00	a2c480c1-5224-4aac-aff6-38388b28c402	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The two most popular certification agencies are <strong>PADI</strong> (Professional Association of Diving Instructors) and <strong>SSI</strong> (Scuba Schools International). Both are recognized worldwide and offer comparable training. The choice often comes down to which agency your local dive shop is affiliated with.</p>"}	2	t	a1ab91bc-f123-44ec-9004-e74c6c92d9cc
2026-01-11 11:05:38.990069+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.990082+00	454cf9cf-316f-4147-882e-32cb6a1c5f7d	\N	heading	{"text": "Course Structure", "level": 2}	3	t	a1ab91bc-f123-44ec-9004-e74c6c92d9cc
2026-01-11 11:05:38.992581+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.992591+00	c6fa5523-bbc5-495b-9e95-316bd7f6e7a6	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The Open Water course typically includes:</p><ul><li><strong>Knowledge Development</strong> - Online or classroom learning covering dive theory</li><li><strong>Confined Water Dives</strong> - Pool sessions to practice skills in controlled environment</li><li><strong>Open Water Dives</strong> - 4 dives in open water demonstrating mastery of skills</li></ul>"}	4	t	a1ab91bc-f123-44ec-9004-e74c6c92d9cc
2026-01-11 11:05:38.995086+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.995098+00	7ae53a03-5222-491f-8451-2cf48c2f99bb	\N	heading	{"text": "Prerequisites", "level": 2}	5	t	a1ab91bc-f123-44ec-9004-e74c6c92d9cc
2026-01-11 11:05:38.997334+00	2026-01-11 11:05:38.997346+00	8e570f25-40c0-4363-be86-4f0742e1ecfa	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>To enroll in an Open Water course, you must:</p><ul><li>Be at least 10 years old (Junior Open Water) or 15 years old (Open Water)</li><li>Be comfortable in the water and able to swim</li><li>Complete a medical questionnaire (some conditions require physician clearance)</li></ul>"}	6	t	a1ab91bc-f123-44ec-9004-e74c6c92d9cc
2026-01-11 11:05:39.006696+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.006706+00	0eaf29c8-72d2-40a8-98bd-4be1464b7f67	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Few underwater encounters are as magical as coming face-to-face with a sea turtle. These ancient mariners have been swimming our oceans for over 100 million years, and as divers, we have the privilege of sharing their underwater world.</p>"}	0	t	9fcbf843-5417-4a36-86ff-1f427d06335b
2026-01-11 11:05:39.008687+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.008697+00	a21552c9-df06-4dbc-a31d-84dd5ac8d497	\N	heading	{"text": "Species You Might Encounter", "level": 2}	1	t	9fcbf843-5417-4a36-86ff-1f427d06335b
2026-01-11 11:05:39.010489+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.010498+00	37f0bc4e-379e-47b7-b10d-4dac39c9b7db	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p><strong>Green Sea Turtle</strong> - The most commonly encountered species, named for the green color of their fat. Often seen grazing on seagrass beds.</p><p><strong>Hawksbill Turtle</strong> - Recognizable by their pointed beak and beautiful patterned shell. Frequently found on coral reefs feeding on sponges.</p><p><strong>Loggerhead Turtle</strong> - Named for their large heads, these powerful swimmers are often seen in temperate waters.</p>"}	2	t	9fcbf843-5417-4a36-86ff-1f427d06335b
2026-01-11 11:05:39.012331+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.012341+00	62d96b4d-cf24-4428-b00e-e705f3cecdf1	\N	heading	{"text": "Responsible Turtle Watching", "level": 2}	3	t	9fcbf843-5417-4a36-86ff-1f427d06335b
2026-01-11 11:05:39.014465+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.014474+00	f4f1262a-1d71-4605-bd21-ddc5ef3fcf9a	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<ul><li>Keep a respectful distance of at least 2 meters (6 feet)</li><li>Never touch, chase, or ride sea turtles</li><li>Avoid blocking their path to the surface - they need to breathe!</li><li>Don't use flash photography</li><li>Let them approach you rather than swimming after them</li></ul>"}	4	t	9fcbf843-5417-4a36-86ff-1f427d06335b
2026-01-11 11:05:39.022756+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.022765+00	102b1085-5713-448e-b74e-884d8f135eb4	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Decompression sickness (DCS), commonly known as \\"the bends,\\" is one of the most serious risks divers face. Understanding what causes it, how to prevent it, and how to recognize symptoms is essential knowledge for every diver.</p>"}	0	t	c1c79b4f-ba39-476e-ab2a-b3d64f6691f2
2026-01-11 11:05:39.025056+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.025065+00	cd40dd76-dfef-4fa3-abd2-c7c56716bfb4	\N	heading	{"text": "What Causes DCS?", "level": 2}	1	t	c1c79b4f-ba39-476e-ab2a-b3d64f6691f2
2026-01-11 11:05:39.026925+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.026935+00	46832208-2516-40a7-a5f3-8015b0789e7b	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>During a dive, nitrogen from the air we breathe dissolves into our body tissues under pressure. If we ascend too quickly, this nitrogen can form bubbles in our tissues and bloodstream, similar to how bubbles form when opening a carbonated drink. These bubbles can cause a range of symptoms from mild joint pain to life-threatening neurological damage.</p>"}	2	t	c1c79b4f-ba39-476e-ab2a-b3d64f6691f2
2026-01-11 11:05:39.028779+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.028788+00	82fc295b-d830-4223-bfc4-227d69a4e2cd	\N	heading	{"text": "Prevention Strategies", "level": 2}	3	t	c1c79b4f-ba39-476e-ab2a-b3d64f6691f2
2026-01-11 11:05:39.03068+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.030688+00	3fd5ef62-bfcf-497f-a9a6-19c534ea61c5	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<ul><li>Always follow your dive computer or tables</li><li>Ascend slowly - no faster than 30 feet (9m) per minute</li><li>Perform safety stops at 15 feet (5m) for 3-5 minutes</li><li>Stay well hydrated before and after diving</li><li>Avoid flying within 18-24 hours after diving</li><li>Don't push no-decompression limits</li></ul>"}	4	t	c1c79b4f-ba39-476e-ab2a-b3d64f6691f2
2026-01-11 11:05:39.03259+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.032598+00	9015673b-cf0b-4f6e-8528-2991b2174bb3	\N	heading	{"text": "Recognizing Symptoms", "level": 2}	5	t	c1c79b4f-ba39-476e-ab2a-b3d64f6691f2
2026-01-12 06:35:52.246615+00	2026-01-12 06:35:52.246638+00	5fee2fb8-d8a4-427f-b3a2-b36c31e4d8cd	\N	hero	{"title": "Dive Into Paradise", "cta_url": "/contact/", "cta_text": "Book Your Dive", "subtitle": "Experience the magic of the Caribbean Sea with Playa del Carmen's friendliest dive team", "background_url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1544551763-46a013bb70d5?w=1920"}	0	t	e0a8c09b-e2d7-4a73-ac53-b5d0e6859d6a
2026-01-11 11:05:39.034412+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.034421+00	e86ea064-43fb-4c76-b39c-192cc270e65c	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Symptoms can appear immediately or up to 24 hours after diving:</p><ul><li>Joint pain (especially shoulders, elbows, knees)</li><li>Fatigue or unusual tiredness</li><li>Skin rash or itching</li><li>Dizziness or vertigo</li><li>Numbness or tingling</li><li>Difficulty breathing</li></ul><p><strong>If you suspect DCS, seek emergency medical care immediately and contact DAN (Divers Alert Network).</strong></p>"}	6	t	c1c79b4f-ba39-476e-ab2a-b3d64f6691f2
2026-01-11 11:05:39.042672+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.042681+00	f7ab03a6-4a01-49c1-8a35-933187e9ccd4	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Coral reefs cover less than 1% of the ocean floor but support approximately 25% of all marine species. As divers, we have a unique connection to these underwater ecosystems and a responsibility to help protect them for future generations.</p>"}	0	t	3f32d60a-de06-42ea-a122-9bc44ac2531b
2026-01-11 11:05:39.044717+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.044728+00	3bc955ff-6aac-4ee5-893c-a53e701d79ce	\N	heading	{"text": "Threats to Coral Reefs", "level": 2}	1	t	3f32d60a-de06-42ea-a122-9bc44ac2531b
2026-01-11 11:05:39.046784+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.046794+00	ab67b707-02a8-476f-9953-dd1f43828d5f	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Coral reefs face numerous threats, both local and global:</p><ul><li><strong>Climate Change</strong> - Rising ocean temperatures cause coral bleaching</li><li><strong>Ocean Acidification</strong> - Absorbed CO2 makes it harder for corals to build skeletons</li><li><strong>Pollution</strong> - Runoff from agriculture and urban areas</li><li><strong>Overfishing</strong> - Disrupts reef ecosystem balance</li><li><strong>Physical Damage</strong> - Anchor damage, careless divers, and destructive fishing practices</li></ul>"}	2	t	3f32d60a-de06-42ea-a122-9bc44ac2531b
2026-01-11 11:05:39.048827+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.048836+00	f7e6137a-335b-4e0f-a411-544833fddd07	\N	heading	{"text": "How Divers Can Help", "level": 2}	3	t	3f32d60a-de06-42ea-a122-9bc44ac2531b
2026-01-11 11:05:39.05067+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.050678+00	f79a2c01-3a24-417a-866f-85355665c083	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<ul><li><strong>Perfect Your Buoyancy</strong> - Good buoyancy control prevents accidental reef contact</li><li><strong>Choose Reef-Safe Sunscreen</strong> - Avoid oxybenzone and octinoxate</li><li><strong>Participate in Reef Cleanups</strong> - Remove debris and fishing line</li><li><strong>Report Marine Life Sightings</strong> - Citizen science helps researchers track reef health</li><li><strong>Support Conservation Organizations</strong> - Donate to or volunteer with reef protection groups</li><li><strong>Spread Awareness</strong> - Share your underwater experiences and educate others</li></ul>"}	4	t	3f32d60a-de06-42ea-a122-9bc44ac2531b
2026-01-11 11:05:39.059756+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.059766+00	58a80315-497b-41ee-94b7-752c5dd9094c	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>It was a cold February evening when I slipped beneath the dark waters of Puget Sound. Night diving in the Pacific Northwest isn't for everyone - the water temperature hovered around 45F (7C), and visibility after sunset can be unpredictable. But something kept drawing me back to these waters, and on this particular night, I would discover why.</p>"}	0	t	b09608ff-9758-4101-bc67-f8281ae75694
2026-01-11 11:05:39.061747+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.061757+00	c4857cb5-ce13-4ad8-bacc-2c6a6fb1f99f	\N	heading	{"text": "The Descent", "level": 2}	1	t	b09608ff-9758-4101-bc67-f8281ae75694
2026-01-11 11:05:39.063694+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.063704+00	8454c43d-102a-4324-8ffc-b06d98556efd	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>My dive buddy and I descended along the rocky wall, our primary lights cutting narrow paths through the darkness. The beam revealed sleeping rockfish tucked into crevices and tiny shrimp whose eyes reflected our lights like scattered stars. At about 40 feet, something unusual caught my attention - a subtle movement in the rocks that didn't match the gentle surge.</p>"}	2	t	b09608ff-9758-4101-bc67-f8281ae75694
2026-01-11 11:05:39.06552+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.06553+00	d80bf26c-2808-4e5d-bf62-323a4e7ef634	\N	heading	{"text": "The Encounter", "level": 2}	3	t	b09608ff-9758-4101-bc67-f8281ae75694
2026-01-11 11:05:39.067322+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.067331+00	ef42d678-61bb-4bf1-acbf-a761c177e638	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I swept my light across the area and there she was - a Giant Pacific Octopus, easily five feet from arm tip to arm tip, watching me with those remarkable, intelligent eyes. Instead of retreating into her den, she seemed curious, extending one arm toward my light while the others remained anchored to the rocks.</p><p>For nearly twenty minutes, we observed each other. She changed colors constantly - from deep red to mottled brown to almost white - and at one point reached out to touch my gloved hand with a single exploring arm. The suckers gripped briefly before releasing, as if testing whether I was friend or food (or perhaps just confused).</p>"}	4	t	b09608ff-9758-4101-bc67-f8281ae75694
2026-01-11 11:05:39.069109+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.069117+00	29dd5deb-7a8b-4f81-bf68-35ac596a6156	\N	heading	{"text": "A Lasting Impression", "level": 2}	5	t	b09608ff-9758-4101-bc67-f8281ae75694
2026-01-11 11:05:39.070919+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.070928+00	6ccad780-67ca-435b-a515-a0d56fe3c8f2	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>That encounter changed how I think about diving and marine life. These creatures aren't just animals to photograph or check off a list - they're individuals with their own curiosity and intelligence. Every dive now feels like an opportunity for connection, a chance to be a guest in someone else's world.</p><p>If you ever get the chance to night dive in the Pacific Northwest, take it. You never know who you might meet in the darkness.</p>"}	6	t	b09608ff-9758-4101-bc67-f8281ae75694
2026-01-11 11:05:39.080585+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.080597+00	db478514-5144-484c-bc7f-c8031339dad0	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Beneath the jungle floor of Mexico's Yucatan Peninsula lies one of the world's most extensive underwater cave systems. These cenotes - natural sinkholes filled with crystal-clear freshwater - offer divers an experience unlike anything else on Earth.</p>"}	0	t	b144e17e-1945-4aa0-b0da-c402162a595e
2026-01-11 11:05:39.082666+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.082675+00	0280d0e6-2775-43a1-9085-8196bedba775	\N	heading	{"text": "What is a Cenote?", "level": 2}	1	t	b144e17e-1945-4aa0-b0da-c402162a595e
2026-01-11 11:05:39.084571+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.08458+00	8d117275-7cb2-4625-9634-7713c8457264	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Cenotes formed over millions of years as rainwater dissolved the limestone bedrock, creating vast underground river systems. When cave ceilings collapsed, they created the open pools we see today. The ancient Maya considered cenotes sacred - gateways to the underworld - and many contain archaeological artifacts.</p>"}	2	t	b144e17e-1945-4aa0-b0da-c402162a595e
2026-01-11 11:05:39.086492+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.086501+00	63bc91f8-6bdc-4306-b098-ba649c6495c7	\N	heading	{"text": "Top Cenotes for Divers", "level": 2}	3	t	b144e17e-1945-4aa0-b0da-c402162a595e
2026-01-11 11:05:39.088402+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.088411+00	b46a8651-fcfb-4562-a415-fb7a9eeee52f	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p><strong>Dos Ojos</strong> - Famous for its two connected caverns with spectacular light effects. Perfect for Open Water divers.</p><p><strong>The Pit</strong> - A stunning 390-foot deep sinkhole with dramatic halocline effects and ancient tree remains.</p><p><strong>Gran Cenote</strong> - Beautiful formations and excellent visibility, ideal for first-time cenote divers.</p><p><strong>Angelita</strong> - Features a ghostly \\"underwater river\\" created by a hydrogen sulfide cloud at 100 feet.</p>"}	4	t	b144e17e-1945-4aa0-b0da-c402162a595e
2026-01-11 11:05:39.090363+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.090372+00	ac2914c0-7c11-478b-aa19-15988e048086	\N	heading	{"text": "Certification Requirements", "level": 2}	5	t	b144e17e-1945-4aa0-b0da-c402162a595e
2026-01-11 11:05:39.09228+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.092289+00	816e3246-f55f-4898-8384-b3c44c2d9f4e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Most cenote dives fall into two categories:</p><ul><li><strong>Cavern Diving</strong> - Stays within the light zone, Open Water certification required. Natural light always visible.</li><li><strong>Cave Diving</strong> - Penetrates beyond natural light. Requires specialized cave diving certification and equipment.</li></ul><p>Always dive with a certified cenote guide - these environments require specific knowledge of the systems.</p>"}	6	t	b144e17e-1945-4aa0-b0da-c402162a595e
2026-01-12 06:35:52.252369+00	2026-01-12 06:35:52.25239+00	c601c8be-63d2-48bd-b10e-e9e20ef78735	\N	heading	{"text": "Our Diving Adventures", "level": 2}	1	t	e0a8c09b-e2d7-4a73-ac53-b5d0e6859d6a
2026-01-09 16:38:29.100269+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.100294+00	8b021051-4f15-4516-afaf-3809a67df64c	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The Dive Operations Dashboard is your central hub for managing daily operations.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Dashboard Statistics</h3>\\n<p>The top of the dashboard displays key metrics:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Registered Divers</strong> - Total active diver profiles in the system</li>\\n    <li><strong>Active Excursions</strong> - Scheduled and in-progress dive trips</li>\\n    <li><strong>Pending Agreements</strong> - Waivers awaiting signature</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Weather Forecast</h3>\\n<p>The dashboard includes a weather widget showing current conditions and forecast for your dive shop location. Wind speed, direction, and conditions help with trip planning decisions.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Quick Navigation</h3>\\n<p>The sidebar provides access to all major sections:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Dive Operations</strong> - Excursions, Divers, Sites, Protected Areas, Agreements, Medical</li>\\n    <li><strong>Planning</strong> - Dive Plans and Dive Logs</li>\\n    <li><strong>System</strong> - Documents, Media, Audit Log</li>\\n    <li><strong>Configuration</strong> - Excursion Types, Agreement Templates, Catalog Items, AI Settings</li>\\n    <li><strong>Finance</strong> - Chart of Accounts, Payables</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	4b6a40ec-8363-4dfb-af98-59224bccb152
2026-01-09 16:38:29.110235+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.110254+00	a1ff52b5-2332-4187-a9f2-6eaf2f4b960f	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The staff portal uses a consistent navigation structure across all pages.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Sidebar Navigation</h3>\\n<p>The left sidebar is organized into logical sections:</p>\\n\\n<h4>Dive Operations</h4>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Excursions</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/excursions/</code>) - Schedule and manage dive trips</li>\\n    <li><strong>Divers</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/divers/</code>) - Diver profiles and certifications</li>\\n    <li><strong>Dive Sites</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/sites/</code>) - Location details and photos</li>\\n    <li><strong>Protected Areas</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/protected-areas/</code>) - Marine parks, permits, fees</li>\\n    <li><strong>Agreements</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/signable-agreements/</code>) - Waivers and contracts</li>\\n    <li><strong>Medical Questionnaires</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/medical/</code>) - Health screening</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h4>Planning</h4>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Dive Plans</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/dive-plans/</code>) - Pre-dive briefings and profiles</li>\\n    <li><strong>Dive Logs</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/dive-logs/</code>) - Post-dive records</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h4>Configuration</h4>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Excursion Types</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/excursion-types/</code>) - Trip templates with pricing</li>\\n    <li><strong>Agreement Types</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/agreements/templates/</code>) - Document templates</li>\\n    <li><strong>Catalog Items</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/catalog/</code>) - Products and services</li>\\n    <li><strong>AI Settings</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/settings/ai/</code>) - AI feature configuration</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h4>Finance</h4>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Chart of Accounts</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/accounts/</code>) - Ledger accounts</li>\\n    <li><strong>Payables</strong> (<code>/staff/diveops/payables/</code>) - Vendor invoices and payments</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	a83d34fc-7785-4ec6-ac37-3a8cd7aff249
2026-01-09 16:38:29.136761+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.13678+00	89c8d3e5-d7c1-49d5-9ee2-9c1d21c0c70b	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The certification system tracks diver qualifications using a normalized model with agency-scoped certification levels.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Certification Levels</h3>\\n<p>Certifications are ranked for eligibility checking:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Scuba Diver</strong> - Entry level (rank 1)</li>\\n    <li><strong>Open Water Diver</strong> - Basic certification (rank 2)</li>\\n    <li><strong>Advanced Open Water</strong> - Intermediate (rank 3)</li>\\n    <li><strong>Rescue Diver</strong> - Advanced (rank 4)</li>\\n    <li><strong>Divemaster</strong> - Professional (rank 5)</li>\\n    <li><strong>Instructor</strong> - Teaching level (rank 6)</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Specialty Certifications</h3>\\n<p>Additional certifications tracked include:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Enriched Air (Nitrox) Diver</li>\\n    <li>Deep Diver</li>\\n    <li>Night Diver</li>\\n    <li>Wreck Diver</li>\\n    <li>Cavern Diver</li>\\n    <li>Underwater Photographer</li>\\n    <li>Peak Performance Buoyancy</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Verification Status</h3>\\n<p>Each certification tracks:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Verification status</strong> - Whether card has been verified</li>\\n    <li><strong>Verified by</strong> - Staff member who verified</li>\\n    <li><strong>Verified at</strong> - Date of verification</li>\\n    <li><strong>Document proof</strong> - Uploaded certification card photo</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Eligibility Checking</h3>\\n<p>When booking divers for excursions, the system automatically checks certification requirements. The <code>is_current</code> property validates expiration dates.</p>"}	0	t	2da48b70-358c-4ef4-94c8-97618b86a909
2026-01-09 16:38:29.145587+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.145608+00	0f2f599b-506e-4a1e-bc57-d8e58fd18eef	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The EmergencyContact model stores emergency contact information with priority ordering for each diver.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Contact Information</h3>\\n<p>Each emergency contact includes:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Name</strong> - Contact's full name</li>\\n    <li><strong>Relationship</strong> - Relationship to diver</li>\\n    <li><strong>Phone numbers</strong> - Primary and alternate contact numbers</li>\\n    <li><strong>Priority</strong> - Order of contact (primary, secondary, etc.)</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Diver Relationships</h3>\\n<p>The DiverRelationship model tracks connections between divers:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Spouse</strong> - Married partner</li>\\n    <li><strong>Buddy</strong> - Preferred dive buddy</li>\\n    <li><strong>Friend</strong> - Social connection</li>\\n    <li><strong>Family</strong> - Family member</li>\\n    <li><strong>Instructor/Student</strong> - Training relationship</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Buddy Preferences</h3>\\n<p>Divers can mark preferred buddies. The system provides methods to query:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><code>spouse</code> - Find spouse relationship</li>\\n    <li><code>preferred_buddies</code> - List marked buddy preferences</li>\\n    <li><code>related_divers</code> - All connected divers</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	6fa98552-ab6d-4615-9eed-c438d73b11a9
2026-01-09 16:38:29.153933+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.153951+00	963653fb-535e-48aa-9774-bc1a4cb02900	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Diver categorization is used for agreement template targeting and eligibility.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Category Types</h3>\\n<p>The DiverCategory enumeration defines:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>all</strong> - Applies to all divers</li>\\n    <li><strong>certified</strong> - Certified divers only</li>\\n    <li><strong>student</strong> - Divers in training</li>\\n    <li><strong>dsd</strong> - Discover Scuba Diving participants</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Agreement Template Targeting</h3>\\n<p>Agreement templates can be configured for specific diver categories. When creating agreements, the system presents only templates appropriate for the diver's category.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Diver Type Classification</h3>\\n<p>Separate from category, divers are classified by their relationship with diving:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Activity</strong> - Does diving as an occasional activity</li>\\n    <li><strong>Identity</strong> - Diving is core to their identity</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>This classification helps with marketing and communication targeting.</p>"}	0	t	ec1dec5d-a7c6-48df-bffb-c392b23cc387
2026-01-12 13:38:34.01259+00	2026-01-12 13:38:34.012605+00	003bba03-b33a-4fc9-9cb8-745e7c255fd1	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Decompression sickness (DCS), commonly known as \\"the bends,\\" is one of the most serious risks divers face. Understanding what causes it, how to prevent it, and how to recognize symptoms is essential knowledge for every diver.</p>"}	0	t	c67b253c-9b18-4541-af18-6f5ea6c519ab
2026-01-12 13:38:34.016087+00	2026-01-12 13:38:34.016103+00	5823a557-00c7-4314-9cb5-f45a060a21b8	\N	heading	{"text": "What Causes DCS?", "level": 2}	1	t	c67b253c-9b18-4541-af18-6f5ea6c519ab
2026-01-09 16:38:29.16144+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.161458+00	499d999c-4263-48ef-93a9-7273b7f54c05	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Excursions are single-day operational units representing scheduled dive trips.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Creating an Excursion</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Navigate to <strong>Excursions</strong></li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>New Excursion</strong></li>\\n    <li>Select an <strong>Excursion Type</strong> (template with defaults)</li>\\n    <li>Set <strong>Date</strong> and <strong>Departure Time</strong></li>\\n    <li>Choose <strong>Dive Site</strong> (optional - can have multiple via dives)</li>\\n    <li>Set <strong>Maximum Divers</strong> capacity</li>\\n    <li>Set <strong>Price per Diver</strong> (pre-filled from type)</li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Create</strong></li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Excursion Types</h3>\\n<p>ExcursionType models serve as templates defining:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Name and description</strong></li>\\n    <li><strong>Dive mode</strong> - boat, shore, cenote, cavern</li>\\n    <li><strong>Time of day</strong> - morning, afternoon, night</li>\\n    <li><strong>Duration</strong> - typical_duration_minutes</li>\\n    <li><strong>Dives per excursion</strong> - number of dives included</li>\\n    <li><strong>Base price</strong> - default pricing</li>\\n    <li><strong>Certification requirements</strong> - minimum level required</li>\\n    <li><strong>Suitable sites</strong> - M2M relationship (empty = all sites)</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Excursion Status Workflow</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>scheduled</strong> - Future trip, accepting bookings</li>\\n    <li><strong>boarding</strong> - Check-in in progress</li>\\n    <li><strong>in_progress</strong> - Trip underway</li>\\n    <li><strong>completed</strong> - Trip finished</li>\\n    <li><strong>cancelled</strong> - Trip cancelled</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Capacity Management</h3>\\n<p>The <code>spots_available</code> property calculates remaining capacity. The <code>is_full</code> property indicates when max_divers is reached.</p>"}	0	t	817f3f1b-2bdc-4b0a-90ed-6a309a444ce1
2026-01-09 16:38:29.170504+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.170524+00	0d5c7bb2-20df-4061-aae2-4a197b96c787	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Bookings link divers to excursions and track reservation lifecycle.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Creating a Booking</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Open the excursion detail page</li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Add Booking</strong></li>\\n    <li>Search for and select a diver</li>\\n    <li>System performs eligibility checks automatically</li>\\n    <li>Confirm the booking</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Booking Status</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>pending</strong> - Reservation made, not confirmed</li>\\n    <li><strong>confirmed</strong> - Booking confirmed</li>\\n    <li><strong>checked_in</strong> - Diver arrived and checked in</li>\\n    <li><strong>cancelled</strong> - Booking cancelled</li>\\n    <li><strong>no_show</strong> - Diver didn't arrive</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Eligibility Checking</h3>\\n<p>Before booking confirmation, the system validates:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Diver has required certification level for excursion type</li>\\n    <li>Medical clearance is current (if required)</li>\\n    <li>Waiver is signed and valid</li>\\n    <li>No scheduling conflicts</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Eligibility Overrides</h3>\\n<p>The EligibilityOverride model allows bypassing requirements:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>One override per booking only</li>\\n    <li>Requires <strong>approved_by</strong> staff member</li>\\n    <li>Requires documented <strong>reason</strong></li>\\n    <li>Tracks which requirement was bypassed</li>\\n    <li>Creates immutable audit trail</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Price Snapshot</h3>\\n<p>The booking captures <code>price_snapshot</code> at creation time. This ensures price immutability even if the excursion price changes later.</p>"}	0	t	4c55f7ac-d243-4732-aef5-0f33e040fb07
2026-01-09 16:38:29.179803+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.179817+00	f597821f-89be-4937-98b3-afcd4a98ad71	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Check-in is managed through the ExcursionRoster model which tracks actual participants.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Check-in Workflow</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Open the excursion on departure day</li>\\n    <li>View the booking list</li>\\n    <li>For each arriving diver, click to mark check-in</li>\\n    <li>System records <code>checked_in_at</code> timestamp and <code>checked_in_by</code> staff</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Roster Roles</h3>\\n<p>Each roster entry can have a role:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Diver</strong> - Customer participant</li>\\n    <li><strong>Divemaster</strong> - Professional leading the dive</li>\\n    <li><strong>Instructor</strong> - Teaching role</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Dive Completion</h3>\\n<p>After the excursion, mark <code>dive_completed</code> status for each participant. Notes can be added to individual roster entries.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Excursion Status Transitions</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Use <strong>Start Excursion</strong> to change status to <code>in_progress</code></li>\\n    <li>Use <strong>Complete Excursion</strong> to change status to <code>completed</code></li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	d44f802e-94eb-49aa-aaaf-afb733c31f32
2026-01-09 16:38:29.190522+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.190546+00	48e4ae0e-4165-4f0a-82d2-b0e601058133	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>ExcursionSeries enables scheduling recurring excursions using RFC 5545 recurrence rules.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Creating a Recurring Series</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Open an existing excursion</li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Make Recurring</strong></li>\\n    <li>Configure the recurrence pattern</li>\\n    <li>Set series defaults (capacity, price, meeting place)</li>\\n    <li>Save the series</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Recurrence Rules</h3>\\n<p>The RecurrenceRule model stores RFC 5545 RRULE strings:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=SA</strong> - Every Saturday</li>\\n    <li><strong>FREQ=DAILY</strong> - Every day</li>\\n    <li><strong>FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=MO,WE,FR</strong> - Monday, Wednesday, Friday</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Series Attributes</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>excursion_type</strong> - Template for generated excursions</li>\\n    <li><strong>dive_site</strong> - Default site</li>\\n    <li><strong>capacity_default</strong> - Default max divers</li>\\n    <li><strong>price_default</strong> - Default price</li>\\n    <li><strong>meeting_place</strong> - Where divers meet</li>\\n    <li><strong>window_days</strong> - How far ahead to generate occurrences</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Series Status</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>draft</strong> - Not yet active</li>\\n    <li><strong>active</strong> - Generating occurrences</li>\\n    <li><strong>paused</strong> - Temporarily stopped</li>\\n    <li><strong>retired</strong> - Permanently ended</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Exceptions</h3>\\n<p>RecurrenceException handles individual date modifications:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>cancelled</strong> - Skip this occurrence</li>\\n    <li><strong>rescheduled</strong> - Move to different time</li>\\n    <li><strong>added</strong> - Extra occurrence</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	9f47b677-b359-4bb5-9b0c-f6db296f4f26
2026-01-09 16:38:29.200709+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.20073+00	fddf353a-2d20-4672-ac82-f0ed7bb2ff2d	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Booking cancellations and financial settlements are handled through the SettlementRecord model.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Cancelling a Booking</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Open the booking</li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Cancel Booking</strong></li>\\n    <li>Booking status changes to <code>cancelled</code></li>\\n    <li><code>cancelled_at</code> timestamp is recorded</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Settlement Types</h3>\\n<p>SettlementRecord tracks financial transactions:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>revenue</strong> - Payment received</li>\\n    <li><strong>refund</strong> - Payment returned</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Idempotent Settlements</h3>\\n<p>Each settlement has a unique <code>idempotency_key</code> preventing duplicate processing. The system generates deterministic keys based on booking and transaction type.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Financial State</h3>\\n<p>Bookings track financial state through:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><code>is_settled</code> - Whether payment is complete</li>\\n    <li><code>has_refund</code> - Whether refund was issued</li>\\n    <li><code>get_financial_state()</code> - Current state summary</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Protection Against Deletion</h3>\\n<p>Settled bookings cannot be deleted to preserve financial records. Use soft delete (<code>deleted_at</code>) instead.</p>"}	0	t	6c3cb5be-f01e-4c18-8fcc-a76b69331c0d
2026-01-09 16:38:29.210522+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.21055+00	653716f6-e872-4926-b35a-29eaa9879190	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>SignableAgreement tracks the full workflow of liability waivers and other documents from creation through signature.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Creating a New Agreement</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Navigate to <strong>Agreements</strong></li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>New Agreement</strong></li>\\n    <li>Select an <strong>Agreement Template</strong> (radio buttons)</li>\\n    <li>Select the <strong>Diver</strong> from the dropdown</li>\\n    <li>Choose <strong>Delivery Method</strong>:\\n        <ul>\\n            <li><em>Link (copy signing URL)</em> - Generate shareable link</li>\\n            <li><em>Email (send to diver)</em> - Email the signing link</li>\\n            <li><em>In Person (sign on device)</em> - Sign at the shop</li>\\n        </ul>\\n    </li>\\n    <li>Set <strong>Expires In</strong> (7, 14, 30, 60, or 90 days)</li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Create & Send</strong> or <strong>Save as Draft</strong></li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Agreement Templates</h3>\\n<p>AgreementTemplate defines reusable document types:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>waiver</strong> - Liability release</li>\\n    <li><strong>medical</strong> - Medical disclosure</li>\\n    <li><strong>briefing</strong> - Dive briefing acknowledgment</li>\\n    <li><strong>code_of_conduct</strong> - Behavior agreement</li>\\n    <li><strong>rental</strong> - Equipment rental terms</li>\\n    <li><strong>training</strong> - Course enrollment</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Template Targeting</h3>\\n<p>Templates can target specific audiences:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>target_party_type</strong> - diver, employee, vendor, any</li>\\n    <li><strong>diver_category</strong> - all, certified, student, dsd</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	a206503a-40de-46ef-abfb-c7cf7851202f
2026-01-09 16:38:29.222448+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.222475+00	1cda68fd-9c55-4854-8574-9373b23ca352	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Agreements use secure token-based access for the signing process.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Access Token Security</h3>\\n<p>Each agreement generates:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Cryptographically random access token</li>\\n    <li>SHA-256 hash stored (raw token never stored)</li>\\n    <li><code>token_consumed</code> flag for one-time use</li>\\n    <li><code>expires_at</code> enforcement at signing time</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Delivery Methods</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Email</strong> - System sends email with secure signing link</li>\\n    <li><strong>Link</strong> - Copy URL to share via text, WhatsApp, etc.</li>\\n    <li><strong>In Person</strong> - Diver signs on shop device</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Resending</h3>\\n<p>For agreements in <code>sent</code> status, use <strong>Resend</strong> to generate a new token and send again. Previous tokens are invalidated.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Expiration Options</h3>\\n<p>Signing links can expire in:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>7 days (default)</li>\\n    <li>14 days</li>\\n    <li>30 days</li>\\n    <li>60 days</li>\\n    <li>90 days</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	77db8ce6-c8ce-46e1-90d9-a01a5679eec7
2026-01-09 16:38:29.234443+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.234471+00	1dcd3b7c-dfb7-46f0-8db8-7976655b0d99	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Monitor agreement progress through the defined status workflow.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Agreement Status</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>draft</strong> - Created but not sent, content editable</li>\\n    <li><strong>sent</strong> - Delivered to signer, awaiting signature</li>\\n    <li><strong>signed</strong> - Completed with digital signature</li>\\n    <li><strong>void</strong> - Cancelled before signing</li>\\n    <li><strong>expired</strong> - Signing link expired without signature</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>List Filtering</h3>\\n<p>The agreements list provides filters to find specific documents:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Filter by status (dropdown)</li>\\n    <li>Search by diver name</li>\\n    <li>Date range filtering</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Agreement Detail View</h3>\\n<p>Each agreement shows:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Status badge with color coding</li>\\n    <li>Diver information</li>\\n    <li>Template used and version</li>\\n    <li>Timeline of status changes</li>\\n    <li>Digital signature details (if signed)</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Content Hash</h3>\\n<p>Agreements maintain a SHA-256 <code>content_hash</code> for integrity verification. Any content changes create revision records.</p>"}	0	t	d1d40dda-b000-4bf7-8d6c-de532960fab4
2026-01-09 16:38:29.246533+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.246558+00	5b5ebc39-bd21-4d8a-8fcd-1c483ec5645f	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Voiding cancels an agreement before it is signed.</p>\\n\\n<h3>When to Void</h3>\\n<p>Void an agreement when:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Created in error</li>\\n    <li>Wrong template selected</li>\\n    <li>Wrong diver associated</li>\\n    <li>Related booking cancelled</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Voiding Restrictions</h3>\\n<p><strong>Important:</strong> Only agreements in <code>draft</code> or <code>sent</code> status can be voided.</p>\\n<p>Signed agreements are legal documents and cannot be voided. To nullify a signed agreement, create a <strong>Revocation Agreement</strong> that the diver must also sign.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Voiding Process</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Open the agreement (must be draft or sent)</li>\\n    <li>Click <strong>Void Agreement</strong></li>\\n    <li>Enter required reason for voiding</li>\\n    <li>Confirm the action</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Revision History</h3>\\n<p>SignableAgreementRevision maintains an immutable audit trail of all content changes, including voiding. Each revision records:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><code>revision_number</code></li>\\n    <li><code>previous</code> and <code>new content_hash</code></li>\\n    <li><code>change_note</code> (required explanation)</li>\\n    <li><code>changed_by</code> staff member</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	fbbf996e-7f3a-41c0-86e0-02aad3c9f38c
2026-01-09 16:38:29.25725+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.257274+00	c6b63eb3-bcee-403c-890b-9483efdb08bc	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Medical questionnaires screen divers for health conditions that may affect diving safety, based on RSTC/DAN Medical Statement guidelines.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Questionnaire List</h3>\\n<p>The medical questionnaires page (<code>/staff/diveops/medical/</code>) displays:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>All submitted questionnaires</li>\\n    <li>Status filters for reviewing</li>\\n    <li>Diver information and submission date</li>\\n    <li>Flagged conditions count</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Sending Questionnaires</h3>\\n<p>Questionnaires can be sent:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>From diver profile medical tab</li>\\n    <li>Automatically when creating first booking</li>\\n    <li>On annual renewal dates</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Integration with django-questionnaires</h3>\\n<p>The medical system uses the django-questionnaires package for form rendering and response collection.</p>"}	0	t	a321255e-4722-483e-8c23-12d3d9ab79c2
2026-01-09 16:38:29.269393+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.269418+00	b022ca57-3f93-4428-ab50-5a1f2d54d5d7	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Staff review completed questionnaires to determine diving eligibility.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Review Workflow</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Navigate to <strong>Medical Questionnaires</strong></li>\\n    <li>Filter for pending review status</li>\\n    <li>Open questionnaire to see all responses</li>\\n    <li>Review flagged conditions</li>\\n    <li>Make clearance decision</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Flagged Conditions</h3>\\n<p>Certain \\"Yes\\" answers automatically flag for review:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Cardiovascular conditions</li>\\n    <li>Respiratory conditions</li>\\n    <li>Neurological conditions (seizures, blackouts)</li>\\n    <li>Diabetes requiring medication</li>\\n    <li>Recent surgery or illness</li>\\n    <li>Current medications</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Medical Status Determination</h3>\\n<p>The <code>get_diver_medical_status()</code> service returns:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>cleared</strong> - Approved for diving</li>\\n    <li><strong>restricted</strong> - Approved with limitations</li>\\n    <li><strong>needs_review</strong> - Requires staff evaluation</li>\\n    <li><strong>denied</strong> - Not approved for diving</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	142dfdb1-3713-45fa-8b40-dca9cf93c178
2026-01-12 13:38:34.019233+00	2026-01-12 13:38:34.019249+00	2f043aa3-55d5-4097-8e4a-1fd975373d04	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>During a dive, nitrogen from the air we breathe dissolves into our body tissues under pressure. If we ascend too quickly, this nitrogen can form bubbles in our tissues and bloodstream, similar to how bubbles form when opening a carbonated drink. These bubbles can cause a range of symptoms from mild joint pain to life-threatening neurological damage.</p>"}	2	t	c67b253c-9b18-4541-af18-6f5ea6c519ab
2026-01-09 16:38:29.280458+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.280476+00	6648a4e9-cbc0-460c-8a2b-3a50e081e2d4	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Physician clearance is required when questionnaire responses indicate potential health concerns.</p>\\n\\n<h3>When Clearance Required</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Questionnaire has flagged responses</li>\\n    <li>Diver reports significant medical conditions</li>\\n    <li>Previous clearance has expired</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Clearance Workflow</h3>\\n<ol>\\n    <li>System generates PDF with flagged conditions</li>\\n    <li>Diver takes form to physician</li>\\n    <li>Physician examines and signs clearance</li>\\n    <li>Diver returns signed form</li>\\n    <li>Staff uploads and records clearance</li>\\n</ol>\\n\\n<h3>Recording Clearance</h3>\\n<p>The DiverProfile stores:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><code>medical_clearance_date</code> - When obtained</li>\\n    <li><code>medical_clearance_valid_until</code> - Expiration</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Medical Provider Integration</h3>\\n<p>The MedicalProviderProfile and MedicalProviderRelationship models track relationships between divers and their healthcare providers.</p>"}	0	t	6de4aa06-1d59-4ae3-8dfc-12bdadc4121d
2026-01-09 16:38:29.291441+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.291458+00	5326cfe8-978c-4973-a8ae-0fa85e647155	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Medical records are subject to retention policies and privacy requirements.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Document Retention</h3>\\n<p>The DocumentRetentionPolicy model manages automatic document lifecycle:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Retention period definition</li>\\n    <li>Automatic purge scheduling</li>\\n    <li>Legal hold capability (DocumentLegalHold)</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Privacy Considerations</h3>\\n<p>Medical information is protected:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Access limited to authorized staff</li>\\n    <li>Audit logging of all access</li>\\n    <li>Secure storage and transmission</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Retention Administration</h3>\\n<p>Staff can manage retention policies through:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>RetentionPolicyListView</li>\\n    <li>RetentionPolicyCreateView</li>\\n    <li>RetentionPolicyUpdateView</li>\\n    <li>RetentionPolicyDeleteView</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	5ee2edec-505d-44a9-8955-0a525ba45f99
2026-01-09 16:38:29.300917+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.300941+00	c6067502-6f1b-4d0d-b77d-c8746cc57404	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>ProtectedArea models represent marine parks, reserves, and other regulated diving areas.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Protected Area Types</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>national_park</strong></li>\\n    <li><strong>marine_park</strong></li>\\n    <li><strong>reserve</strong></li>\\n    <li><strong>biosphere_reserve</strong></li>\\n    <li><strong>protected_area</strong></li>\\n    <li><strong>sanctuary</strong></li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Hierarchical Structure</h3>\\n<p>Protected areas support hierarchy through self-referential parent relationships. The <code>get_ancestors()</code> method returns the parent chain.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Unified Permit System</h3>\\n<p>ProtectedAreaPermit handles all permit types:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>guide</strong> - Guide credential (requires diver)</li>\\n    <li><strong>vessel</strong> - Boat permit (requires vessel_name, vessel_registration)</li>\\n    <li><strong>photography</strong> - Commercial photography permit</li>\\n    <li><strong>diving</strong> - Operator diving permit</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Permit Attributes</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><code>permit_number</code> - Unique per area+type</li>\\n    <li><code>issued_at</code>, <code>expires_at</code> - Validity period</li>\\n    <li><code>authorized_zones</code> - M2M (empty = all zones)</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	2739e7d1-a6e1-443e-aaa2-ca0c4d6ae870
2026-01-09 16:38:29.310113+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.310131+00	db3e5613-d266-4ec5-9e31-41ca9e987a0c	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>ProtectedAreaFeeSchedule configures fees for diving activities in protected areas.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Fee Types</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>per_person</strong> - Charged per diver</li>\\n    <li><strong>per_boat</strong> - Charged per vessel</li>\\n    <li><strong>per_trip</strong> - Charged per excursion</li>\\n    <li><strong>per_day</strong> - Daily fee</li>\\n    <li><strong>per_activity</strong> - Activity-specific fee</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Activity Scope</h3>\\n<p>Fees can apply to:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>diving</li>\\n    <li>snorkeling</li>\\n    <li>kayaking</li>\\n    <li>fishing</li>\\n    <li>all activities</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Fee Tiers</h3>\\n<p>ProtectedAreaFeeTier allows tiered pricing:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>tourist</strong> - Standard tourist rate</li>\\n    <li><strong>national</strong> - National citizen rate</li>\\n    <li><strong>local</strong> - Local resident rate</li>\\n    <li><strong>student</strong> - Student discount</li>\\n    <li><strong>senior</strong> - Senior discount</li>\\n    <li><strong>child</strong> - Child rate (age_min, age_max)</li>\\n    <li><strong>infant</strong> - Infant (usually free)</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Eligibility Proof</h3>\\n<p>DiverEligibilityProof tracks documentation for tier qualification:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Proof types: student_id, national_id, resident_card, passport, birth_cert</li>\\n    <li>Status: pending, verified, rejected</li>\\n    <li>Expiration tracking for time-limited proofs</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	d87e9555-6676-4856-9f3d-1e4ea2e3f207
2026-01-09 16:38:29.319651+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.319672+00	c3303797-0911-4de0-8d84-ffd947464c1e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>ProtectedAreaZone divides protected areas into zones with specific regulations.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Zone Types</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>core</strong> - No-take zone, highest protection</li>\\n    <li><strong>buffer</strong> - Buffer zone around core</li>\\n    <li><strong>use</strong> - Recreational use zone</li>\\n    <li><strong>restoration</strong> - Restoration area</li>\\n    <li><strong>research</strong> - Research-only access</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Zone Permissions</h3>\\n<p>Each zone defines:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><code>diving_allowed</code></li>\\n    <li><code>anchoring_allowed</code></li>\\n    <li><code>fishing_allowed</code></li>\\n    <li><code>requires_guide</code></li>\\n    <li><code>requires_permit</code></li>\\n    <li><code>max_divers</code> - Capacity limit</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Zone Rules</h3>\\n<p>ProtectedAreaRule enforces specific regulations:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Rule types</strong>: max_depth, max_divers, certification, equipment, time, activity, conduct</li>\\n    <li><strong>Applies to</strong>: diver, group, vessel, operator</li>\\n    <li><strong>Enforcement levels</strong>: info, warn, block</li>\\n    <li><strong>Effective dating</strong>: effective_start, effective_end</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Compliance Checking</h3>\\n<p>Rules use comparison operators (lte, gte, eq, in, contains, required_true) against values. The system can block bookings that violate blocking-level rules.</p>"}	0	t	1092d33c-b7f0-4fc4-874e-db692be2c942
2026-01-09 16:38:29.328985+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.329018+00	1398c2a1-51cc-465a-a4ee-31c30a4b1b41	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The document browser (<code>/staff/diveops/documents/</code>) provides file storage and organization.</p>\\n\\n<h3>Document Browser Features</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Folder-based organization</li>\\n    <li>File upload and download</li>\\n    <li>Preview for common file types</li>\\n    <li>Search functionality</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Document Types Used</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li><strong>Certification cards</strong> - Proof of diver certification</li>\\n    <li><strong>Profile photos</strong> - Diver identification</li>\\n    <li><strong>Dive site photos</strong> - Site documentation and marketing</li>\\n    <li><strong>Signature documents</strong> - Captured signatures</li>\\n    <li><strong>Signed agreement PDFs</strong> - Completed waivers</li>\\n    <li><strong>Medical clearances</strong> - Physician letters</li>\\n    <li><strong>Eligibility proofs</strong> - ID documents for fee tiers</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Folder Management</h3>\\n<p>Views for folder organization:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>FolderCreateView, FolderUpdateView, FolderDeleteView</li>\\n    <li>FolderPermissionListView for access control</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Soft Delete</h3>\\n<p>Documents use soft delete with a trash feature:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>DocumentDeleteView moves to trash</li>\\n    <li>DocumentRestoreView recovers from trash</li>\\n    <li>DocumentPermanentDeleteView for final deletion</li>\\n    <li>EmptyTrashView clears all trashed documents</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	05c8f67a-89f2-402b-a979-4162e3c3a242
2026-01-12 13:38:34.022661+00	2026-01-12 13:38:34.022677+00	6e153e53-3758-4acc-90de-9ace3ff12cf8	\N	heading	{"text": "Prevention Strategies", "level": 2}	3	t	c67b253c-9b18-4541-af18-6f5ea6c519ab
2026-01-09 16:38:29.3406+00	2026-01-09 16:38:29.340622+00	783d0de0-f403-4b87-bd99-0d59341bfc43	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The audit log (<code>/staff/diveops/audit-log/</code>) tracks all system activity for accountability and troubleshooting.</p>\\n\\n<h3>What's Logged</h3>\\n<p>The django-audit-log package records:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Record creation, updates, and deletions</li>\\n    <li>Status changes (booking confirmed, agreement signed, etc.)</li>\\n    <li>User actions with timestamps</li>\\n    <li>IP addresses and user agents</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Viewing the Log</h3>\\n<p>The AuditLogView displays entries with filtering:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Date range</li>\\n    <li>User who performed action</li>\\n    <li>Action type</li>\\n    <li>Record type (model)</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Entry Details</h3>\\n<p>Each audit entry includes:</p>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Timestamp</li>\\n    <li>Actor (user who performed action)</li>\\n    <li>Action description</li>\\n    <li>Affected record</li>\\n    <li>Before/after values for changes</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<h3>Use Cases</h3>\\n<ul>\\n    <li>Investigate who made a change</li>\\n    <li>Track workflow progression</li>\\n    <li>Verify compliance actions</li>\\n    <li>Debug issues</li>\\n    <li>Security monitoring</li>\\n</ul>"}	0	t	211b629f-f71f-4fbc-be91-561bbbd7be7b
