2026-01-12 15:31:00.903564+00	2026-01-12 15:31:00.903571+00	a89f13b7-b506-4079-9f4e-8b4d9246198e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Well I'm not gonna be diving for a few days.  Mostly because of my big toe that's scraped up prob gonna lose that nail so fins are a no go.  I'll save you from having to see that injury</p><p>I had a very lucky bike accident yesterday when my front wheel and fork had a malfunction and I faceplanted it in slow motion into the street. Still got all my teeth and my chin didn't split open just scraped up and bruised.  The rest of the road rash sucks but it'll heal fine.  Thank my lucky stars.</p><p>I'm looking for a new fork for my road bike.  And next time I go to the states I'm going to find an old Large size Gary Fisher Big Sur, put street slicks on it, maybe extend the cockpit, and bring it back.  Unless someone has a better suggestion.  My old one in st louis was my fave until it got stolen</p>"}	0	t	e5f2e11f-26fd-45d5-8674-13934d58a579
2026-01-12 15:31:00.911151+00	2026-01-12 15:31:00.911158+00	3df7dde1-5837-436b-be30-6e7325a96e95	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>After losing a camera (again) with a double-ender I've changed to a boltsnap which is what I should have done and I knew I should have in the beginning.  But I didn't have an extra boltsnap yet.</p><p>Also using a double-ender was also breaking one of the rules of safe rigging which is never have a metal to metal connection due to entanglement and being unable to cut free the stuck connection.</p><p>I'm 2 for 2 though.  I was able to go back down and find them.  But I think it's time to stop pushing my luck.  I'm phasing out as many double-ender as I can.  Aside from being necessary with finger spools for dsmbs and jumps in cave navigation,, and (arguably ineffective) for tapping a tank to get someone's attention, double-enders are an untrustworthy and potentially dangerous crutch.</p><p>I use line instead of zip ties because zip ties while strong against direct forces they  easily break with twisting/sheering forces.</p><p>I learned how to tie boltsnaps starting here.  https://youtu.be/Qm_oZTAqE04</p>"}	0	t	a3b1516d-e35a-4112-82f1-5239cb19be5f
