2026-01-12 15:31:00.961703+00	2026-01-12 15:31:00.961711+00	0ea45aad-e92f-4d5d-ada2-47b1d5a92801	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Part of what attracted me to the study of diving is the science.</p><p>I'm certified to teach enriched air diving and emergency oxygen providers.</p><p>But long before I travelled the road to becoming an instructor I was very curious about the physical and chemical properties of oxygen, and how to be aware of and avoid any accidents.  Because accidents with high concentrations of oxygen are surprisingly easy to create.</p><p>We can thank NASA for making and documenting many of those mistakes.  Who better than NASA would know all about accidentally blowing shit up with oxygen.</p><p>A couple years ago when I was exploring the topic I read this 288 page manual on safety.  It's pretty awesome how just a little friction in the bend of a pipe can start the stainless steel on fire. Who woulda thought?!</p><p>So if you're O2 curious and want a little more down in the trenches information than you get in the NITROX course I recommend you read this.  Especially if you're as big of a nerd about the science of accidents as I am.</p><p>https://ntrs.nasa.gov/api/citations/19960021046/downloads/19960021046.pdf</p>"}	0	t	dcca724e-3695-4ab2-a2e0-05252525a6ca
2026-01-12 15:31:00.969173+00	2026-01-12 15:31:00.969181+00	4644e40a-b8eb-4c1e-abd6-e23a735ec944	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Needs more tinkering. Need to make some adjustments to the bands and bungies.  My xdeep kit I bought  is missing a couple pieces of hardware I'm in the process of replacing so the wing is still floppy stupid, and I'm a bit overweighted.  Try try again till I get it right.  I puked a ton on the boat today too. Was looking forward to calling it early after just 1 dive to the wreck. On the line banging around I lost my camera because I used a double ender.  So I waited a surface interval bobbing around on the boat while puking more till I couldn't puke any more.  I was more mad at myself for not being able to book it back ashore and instead I suffered the worst seasickness I've had in years while I waited to go back down and find my camera.  Blah.  I hate that I get seasick, I even took 2 difenidols that didn't seem to make a difference.  Not really very fun diving day at all.  But at least I learned some things and am going to change to a boltsnap attached to the camera with some cave line instead of a double ender.  Double enders always lose shit.  This is the second time I've lost a camera on this wreck and had to go back to get it.  Also mental note: drinking gatorade and puking is horrible.</p>"}	0	t	9b96cbc5-57c2-43dd-bac2-688490dff2ad
