2026-01-12 15:31:01.204371+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.204379+00	8ed927a2-9f86-4150-b5a8-23391be9885f	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I went diving a couple days ago and have started practicing more macro underwater photography with small fish like this Carribbean Sharpnose Puffer.  When you see them in the water they are about the size of a pinky finger and their colors and markings are hard to see.  Up close I think these are some really amazingly beautiful fish.</p><p>They are difficult to photograph because they are very shy and turn away quickly.  I find it's helpful to stay in one spot and wait for them to come around and start being kinda curious. It takes a lot of patience.</p><p>Fui a bucear hace un par de d\\\\u00edas y he empezado a practicar m\\\\u00e1s la fotograf\\\\u00eda macro con peces peque\\\\u00f1os como este Puffer Caribe\\\\u00f1o de Nariz Aguda. Cuando los ves en el agua tienen aproximadamente el tama\\\\u00f1o de un dedo me\\\\u00f1ique y sus colores y marcas son dif\\\\u00edciles de ver. De cerca, creo que estos son peces realmente hermosos.</p><p>Son dif\\\\u00edciles de fotografiar porque son muy t\\\\u00edmidos y se alejan r\\\\u00e1pidamente. Me ha resultado \\\\u00fatil quedarme en un lugar y esperar a que vengan y empiecen a ser un poco curiosos. Se necesita mucha paciencia.</p>"}	0	t	755d7520-e59f-46ba-b357-9fdc388dd49f
