2026-01-12 15:31:01.274246+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.274253+00	76da19dc-2807-40d0-bdea-557a33d3c71e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>If you come to Riviera Maya and decide to visit me in Puerto Morelos, I will take you to get some of the best tacos in town.</p><p>These tacos are not in the touristic port side.  They are in Villas La Playa at a little taco spot named Mariachi.</p>"}	0	t	d6d50b0d-8fb7-425a-ae8a-07db97cb3ffe
2026-01-12 15:31:01.28171+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.281717+00	caa1ea59-8261-4f9d-8268-c9edc7670385	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I was told by my PADI course director that once I get 10 tanks I'm pretty set for teaching small classes.  So over time I've been buying them when they've been offered.</p><p>I normally keep most of them stored at the fill station here because Pro Aire provides delivery services to the pier or a few locations on the beach.  It's super convenient and awesome that those guys do that for us</p><p>But it's also important that I make my tanks easily identifiable. So at their suggestion I've started an art project that should make my tanks really stick out and look awesome.</p><p>Phase one is painting the tops.  Phase 2 is painting the trademarked gay dive buddy happy diving flag in a nice visible location when the tank is in use in the water.  Phase 3 will be cutting stencils of some cool sea creatures and spray paint stenciling to really make them cool.</p><p>Here are some progress pics.  Waiting for the paint to dry is the hardest part!</p>"}	0	t	47286eb3-f63c-4a27-9fe5-6760a0c6b9cf
2026-01-12 15:31:01.288819+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.288829+00	e4a6c760-250a-45d2-80e9-a5050dfb8d1b	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>During every dive, managing and monitoring your air by keeping an eye on your gauge regularly is one of the best things you can do to stay safe.</p><p>Here are a few tips:\\n\\\\ud83d\\\\udca8 Verify air is turned on right before jumping in the water. Make sure to do this by taking a few complete breaths and watching your gauge/watch for any changes.</p><p>\\\\u2b07\\\\ufe0f Ensure you have enough air for your dive (i.e., leave enough air for the return, 1/2 or 1/3 rule).</p><p>\\\\ud83d\\\\udc40 While diving, check your gauge/watch regularly and stay close to your buddy.</p><p>\\\\u270b\\\\ud83c\\\\udffd Make a complete stop (safety or decompression) with at least 500 psi/50 bar remaining.</p><p>What other tips would you add to this list?</p><p>#diversalertnetwork #dan #scuba #scubadiving #scubadiver #scubatrips #underwater #ocean #air #tips #gauge #vacation #bubbles</p>"}	0	t	806a9849-e6ed-4d3e-ab3b-e4039750bd6f
2026-01-12 15:31:01.296887+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.296896+00	c264acc2-19a2-4fdb-829d-a6b5996d413e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The boat ride to our dive site!!</p><p>#happydiving #ScubaDiving #padi #padiinstructor #puertomorelos</p>"}	0	t	303f347f-0769-4963-99ec-ee87d0531596
2026-01-12 15:31:01.304637+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.304644+00	dcb9519b-06d1-4a8a-b713-fab2660a6a5c	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Nurse shark we found on our 2nd dive today.</p><p>Nurse sharks are obligate suction feeders capable of generating suction forces that are among the highest recorded for any aquatic vertebrate to date.  Although their small mouths may limit the size of prey, they can exhibit a suck-and-spit behavior and/or shake their head violently to reduce the size of food items.</p><p>As inoffensive as nurse sharks may appear, they are ranked fourth in documented shark bites on humans likely due to incautious behavior by divers on account of the nurse shark's slow, sedentary nature.</p><p>Tibur\\\\u00f3n nodriza. Los tiburones nodriza son comedores de succi\\\\u00f3n obligados capaces de generar fuerzas de succi\\\\u00f3n que se encuentran entre las m\\\\u00e1s altas registradas para cualquier vertebrado acu\\\\u00e1tico hasta la fecha. Aunque sus bocas peque\\\\u00f1as pueden limitar el tama\\\\u00f1o de la presa, pueden exhibir un comportamiento de chupar y escupir y/o sacudir la cabeza violentamente para reducir el tama\\\\u00f1o de los alimentos.</p><p>A pesar de lo inofensivos que pueden parecer los tiburones nodriza, ocupan el cuarto lugar en las mordeduras documentadas de tiburones en humanos, probablemente debido al comportamiento imprudente de los buzos debido a la naturaleza lenta y sedentaria del tibur\\\\u00f3n nodriza.</p>"}	0	t	25098f10-af89-4ee6-9d59-ec08d3ac94e5
2026-01-12 15:31:01.312521+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.312526+00	c8061c0e-f271-48c8-92c5-cc4b366dcad2	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Getting ready for open water certification dive #4.  Our plan is 18m .  Then followed by a fun dive to practice buyancy and good buddy habits.  We couldn't have asked for a more beautiful day here in this tropical paradise.  Fun in the sun and adventure under the waves awaits!!</p><p>#happydiving</p>"}	0	t	07a6c967-b911-4f46-8d29-226769a9ee6e
