2026-01-12 15:31:01.36372+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.363725+00	8b846f0e-d9b4-46c9-bcbf-beae92e3d23d	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Diver Fight Club \\\\ud83e\\\\udd4a</p><p>A group of divers on an 80-foot ocean drift witness an altercation between one of the divers and their guide.</p><p>Read more about this incident here: https://dan.org/safety-prevention/diver-safety/case-summaries/diver-fight-club/.</p><p>#diversalertnetwork #dan #scuba #scubadiving #underwater #fighting #incident #safetyfirst #fightclub</p>"}	0	t	5f231bc3-f3f9-43cd-81dc-d8b610eaf67c
2026-01-12 15:31:01.369546+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.369551+00	0c64a051-cb6a-45b0-9c35-ed776c0429bd	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Today's Lesson is about not forgetting things.</p>"}	0	t	e44a08fc-535d-4648-aa0a-2a2c7484225b
2026-01-12 15:31:01.375081+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.375085+00	c1f18f71-1ea4-4116-87fe-37e29859f135	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Anticipating my return to Mexico.  Bringing some diving equipment like my drysuit and a new primary reel for wreck.</p><p>I'm also packing a necessary teaching aid for Emergency First Response CPR training.  More people need to get certified in lifesaving CPR!.</p><p>If you have questions about CPR training I'd be more to help answer them about the PADI EFR, and Emergency Oxygen Provider courses that I'm certified to teach.  I can also help you find a course being offered near you.</p><p>EFR training is not just for divers it's for everyone!  It's a fun course and you learn a lot</p>"}	0	t	9c00f057-1da8-4074-bc29-905cffac7331
2026-01-12 15:31:01.380617+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.380622+00	dfe1da68-dd63-4ffb-8f8a-da5fc22cacdf	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>As my visit to the USA enters it's last week thoughts of diving are entering my mind.  One thing I love about the activity is that is how it requires more than just physical skills and athleticism but also dedication to academic and intellectually challenging knowledge about theory, life support systems and physiics.  This article appeared in wired magazine and does an excellent job explaining some of the science.</p>"}	0	t	dfa136b9-4eaf-43a2-8e4b-5f0ac4ccf27c
2026-01-12 15:31:01.386265+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.386269+00	c1cd0b36-985b-4edc-9c33-e53e2f6ccd21	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I went to Isla Mujeres yesterday to go diving with three friends from the USA who were on a vacation together on the Island.  We went to Pocna, a fantastic dive operator on the island that was referred by my course director.</p><p>The journey was new to me as I've never been to Isla Mujeres, and I haven't been traveling in Cancun on my own.  But I figured it out.  Which collectivo's to take where to transfer, get on the ferry, walk to find the dive shop.</p><p>On the walk I saw some great art in this cute town.  It was my first time there so I took some photos along the way.  The street art was neat especially on the building where the dive shop is located.</p>"}	0	t	314b9f4a-f3cd-4073-bd94-bff89d05de4e
2026-01-12 15:31:01.391745+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.39175+00	c125c008-00b2-49d8-b9e2-4673be453db0	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Today I'm on adventure to Isla Mujeres to go dive with three guys from the USA.  The collectivos and ferry ride is pretty easy for my first time.   The water is beautiful today</p>"}	0	t	b26a0f21-d0be-41d5-a994-b9911eb8aae4
2026-01-12 15:31:01.396944+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.396949+00	8b905be4-1319-4489-8fe9-3f37efb1b345	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>On days I'm not diving I maintain my equipment.  I need to buy an ultrasonic cleaner down here in Mexico.  But a bath of vinegar dawn soap water and a toothbrush will do for now.  Luckily this old Sherwood regulator is super easy to take apart and has never been used in salt water.  I think replacing a worn O ring and a good cleaning it'll be ready for diving.  Hopefully it doesn't Do a Challenger rocket booster disaster.  I took the equipment speciality instructor course where we learned on Scubapro MK2s.  This Sherwood is even simpler.  Practice makes perfect.</p>"}	0	t	5906dea2-98e4-468b-8904-2b650d16400f
2026-01-12 15:31:01.402143+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.402148+00	f07ba311-a40a-4fb7-890e-0513249ed272	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Today I saw two Green Moray eels.  I'm getting a little less spooked feeling around them.  I think the feeling I have of being creeped out getting close to them is starting to fade a little.  In fact I noticed that the larger of the two was less interested in me than I was in it and it retreated farther into it's den when it was tired of it's picture being taken.</p><p>While I don't think I'd ever want to pet or snuggle with one of these, the more I'm encountering them the less I feel like I'm about to get attacked.  They are just hella scary looking with those teeth and their internal jaw of teeth a la the movie Aliens.  True fact, they have extendable pharyngeal jaws.  Look it up.</p>"}	0	t	0d3b99ae-8e86-4a0b-9d24-1b76387d23c4
2026-01-12 15:31:01.407679+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.407684+00	6fce1515-5fb6-45ac-9a5c-5e2e1ce70f00	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I have this sidekick.  My friends call him Mr Pickles.  When I'm not diving me and him go on adventures.    #tatumtime</p>"}	0	t	b2619030-e737-4ae6-a624-088b2d365310
2026-01-12 15:31:01.413458+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.413463+00	6031c973-0f1c-4ce0-9eae-2ddbf84ba03c	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Went diving yesterday with a couple friends.  We saw a ton of stuff. On the way down we were startled with a surprise stingray camouflaged in the grass that appeared suddenly out of the silt.  But when I was taking it's photo it didn't care it let me get super close and didn't care one bit when I sailed over it.</p><p>We navigated to many of the coral formations and other interesting features of the dive site.  Despite the poorer visibility that day we were able to find some pretty large schools of fish.  We were able to swim with the resident school of Atlantic Spade fish which was super fun, they were all over us.</p><p>I hadn't seen the large Moray Eel in a while.  But there it was near the end of the dive tucked under one of the corals.  Unfortunately the lighting wasn't super great and I felt kind of apprehensive about getting in super close with the camera in its face for a good shot.  Maybe in the future I'll get more courage or else I'll learn better lighting and when the visibility is much better.</p><p>---</p><p>Fui a bucear ayer con un par de amigos. Vimos un mont\\\\u00f3n de cosas. En el camino hacia abajo nos sorprendi\\\\u00f3 una mantarraya camuflada en la hierba que apareci\\\\u00f3 repentinamente del limo. Pero cuando estaba tomando la foto, no le import\\\\u00f3, me dej\\\\u00f3 acercarme mucho y no le import\\\\u00f3 ni un poco cuando navegu\\\\u00e9 sobre ella.</p><p>Navegamos a muchas de las formaciones de coral y otras caracter\\\\u00edsticas interesantes del sitio de buceo. A pesar de la poca visibilidad ese d\\\\u00eda, pudimos encontrar algunos bancos de peces bastante grandes. Pudimos nadar con la escuela residente de peces Atlantic Spade, que fue muy divertido, estaban sobre nosotros.</p><p>No hab\\\\u00eda visto la gran Moray Eel en mucho tiempo. Pero all\\\\u00ed estaba, cerca del final de la inmersi\\\\u00f3n, escondido debajo de uno de los corales. Desafortunadamente, la iluminaci\\\\u00f3n no era muy buena y me sent\\\\u00ed un poco aprensivo acerca de acercarme mucho a la c\\\\u00e1mara para obtener una buena toma. Tal vez en el futuro me anime m\\\\u00e1s o de lo contrario aprender\\\\u00e9 a iluminar mejor y cuando la visibilidad sea mucho mejor.</p>"}	0	t	a23c95f4-22f4-434c-949a-dfc0976f7c20
2026-01-12 15:31:01.419279+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.419283+00	03d45fe7-0f8f-41dc-bea5-2049a56597bb	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>That dive site under the rainbow.  Ese sitio de buceo bajo el arco\\\\u00edris.</p>"}	0	t	7caef828-b1bc-4bdf-b8e7-2ff506b5cb72
2026-01-12 15:31:01.42505+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.425054+00	c353d4e6-14ff-45ac-839f-22a4c4d54e28	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I post a lot of photos of fish so maybe I need to start showing folks what the town is like.  I took some snapshots along my walk near the pier in Puerto Morelos.  Here you can see some of the restaurants and the town square and the beach along my walk.</p><p>---</p><p>Publico muchas fotos de peces, as\\\\u00ed que tal vez necesito comenzar a mostrarle a la gente c\\\\u00f3mo es la ciudad. Tom\\\\u00e9 algunas instant\\\\u00e1neas durante mi caminata cerca del muelle en Puerto Morelos. Aqu\\\\u00ed puedes ver algunos de los restaurantes y la plaza del pueblo y la playa a lo largo de mi paseo.</p>"}	0	t	6a228104-f3b4-44e7-bd60-3147c7cd1831
2026-01-12 15:31:01.430794+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.430799+00	c38d8209-2a9d-4bfd-a987-8162e7700032	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Photographing Victor Photographing.  Fotografiando Victor Fotografiando.</p>"}	0	t	f187b66d-32ff-4bb5-9e7a-b63152fe4680
2026-01-12 15:31:01.436752+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.436756+00	77efcbc0-6bde-480d-a113-da9242e5f2c4	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>If you're stuck at home inside this Saturday afternoon and want to explore some African American history and archeology while virtually diving a shipwreck this might be something you'll enjoy</p><p>Diving For The Clotilda: The Archaeology, History, And Legacy Of The Last Known Slave Ship</p><p>Join us on Saturday, October 15 for Diving for the Clotilda: The Archaeology, History, and Legacy of the Last Known Slave Ship, a special virtual event where we\\\\u2019ll explore the wreck of the infamous slave ship discovered in 2019 in the Mobile River in Alabama. You\\\\u2019ll hear from the archaeologists exploring the shipwreck, the historians researching its history, and the descendants of the people who were brought over on the ship, as they work to preserve the Clotilda and ensure that its legacy and its stories are not forgotten</p>"}	0	t	c94304c0-7008-436f-aba5-c997da92e5b2
2026-01-12 15:31:01.442971+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.442977+00	fe481a47-9bfe-4607-ad5c-8f48cefdfdd9	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>It's Official.  Full Cave Diver.  Certified to dive safely within my limits with other (more) experienced divers, follow the rules, and avoid injury or death.</p><p>I was motivated to continue my training to this level in order to be a better diver for myself and others.  Not a hotshot, not to massage my ego, not for any adrenaline rush or high risk sports.  Rather to have the knowledge and tools to survive.  Plus I'm a huge nerd and I think learning about diving is super interesting and cool.</p><p>---</p><p>Es oficial. Buceador de cueva completa. Certificado para bucear de forma segura dentro de mis l\\\\u00edmites con otros buceadores (m\\\\u00e1s) experimentados, seguir las reglas y evitar lesiones o la muerte.</p><p>Estaba motivado para continuar mi entrenamiento hasta este nivel para ser un mejor buceador para m\\\\u00ed y para los dem\\\\u00e1s. Ni un hotshot, ni para masajear mi ego, ni para un subid\\\\u00f3n de adrenalina ni para deportes de alto riesgo. M\\\\u00e1s bien tener el conocimiento y las herramientas para sobrevivir. Adem\\\\u00e1s, soy un gran nerd y creo que aprender a bucear es s\\\\u00faper interesante y genial.</p>"}	0	t	cfc5a99d-b106-48c4-9f5f-7e9cc68aa092
2026-01-12 15:31:01.449344+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.449349+00	932bc900-c4b7-47c0-8442-531e8d71234d	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>DAN Medic Ben Strelnick recently presented on Remote Injury Management for Bonaire Tek 2022, an annual event centered on technical diving held by Buddy Dive Resort. This year\\\\u2019s gathering featured speakers from DAN, DiveRite, Shearwater, Fathom Dive Systems/Karst Underwater Research, and Sonardyne.\\\\ud83d\\\\udc68\\\\u200d\\\\ud83c\\\\udfeb</p><p>While on location, Ben completed his crossover training on the O2ptima CM rebreather with the President and CEO of Dive Rite, Lamar Hires, and is now certified to utilize it with Helitrox and decompression techniques to a maximum depth of 150 feet.</p><p>A huge thank you and congratulations to Ben for presenting, completing his training, and continuing to work his regular on-call shift while in Bonaire! \\\\ud83d\\\\udc4f\\\\ud83c\\\\udffd</p><p>Even while having a fun-filled week, our DAN Medics are always ready to take emergency calls. \\\\u260e</p><p>#DiversAlertNetwork #DAN #scuba #scubadiver #scubadive #scubadiving #medic #emergency #calls</p>"}	0	t	72df81f6-7c04-4a7d-b591-318ab14510c6
2026-01-12 15:31:01.455406+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.45541+00	31318a20-d19a-4631-a532-61490b27a96e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Post full cave certification course completion celebration with my favorite buddy Alberto.  Much thanks to him for all the support and encouragement.  And super proud of him for completing his Enriched Air Diver certification and getting started on his Wreck Diver course!  Marlin and shrimp tacos (10 for 280 pesos or about $16.00) and cervesas at Las Koras.  If you visit me I will take you here.  Super delish!</p><p>---</p><p>Despu\\\\u00e9s de la celebraci\\\\u00f3n de la finalizaci\\\\u00f3n del curso completo de certificaci\\\\u00f3n de cuevas con mi amigo favorito Alberto. Muchas gracias a \\\\u00e9l por todo el apoyo y los \\\\u00e1nimos. \\\\u00a1Y s\\\\u00faper orgulloso de \\\\u00e9l por completar su certificaci\\\\u00f3n Enriched Air Diver y comenzar su curso Wreck Diver! Tacos de marlin y camarones (10 por 280 pesos o alrededor de $16.00) y cervesas en Las Koras. Si me visitas te llevo aqu\\\\u00ed. \\\\u00a1S\\\\u00faper delicioso!</p>"}	0	t	c2d77896-6bcc-4dc2-b00c-bb3405f0e89f
2026-01-12 15:31:01.461499+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.461504+00	a404f968-1e83-4bf7-a152-ae213ae4e79c	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Bow and Gun of the Juan Escutia C-56 (formerly the USS Knave AM-256).  Admiral class minesweeper.  One of my favorite dives.</p><p>Last week as the hurricane passed we dove it in very low visibility which makes it super spooky like a ghost ship.  Luckily she was purposely sunk to create an artificial reef and scuba diving playground in Parque Nacional Arrecife de Puerto Morelos and no souls were lost.</p>"}	0	t	39adb4db-bf15-4f8b-b054-5c7ed74f2061
2026-01-12 15:31:01.466899+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.466903+00	6377b265-41a1-4c7d-8d7b-b03ec6535bb7	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Sometimes I photograph the professional photographer.  Especially when he's my buddy Raul, and it's his day off, and we're on a fun dive to the wreck with his friends from Puerto Vallarta.</p><p>I really need to figure out the white balance at depth with this new camera.  I hope he gives me another tutorial.</p>"}	0	t	01b0c3c1-6ea8-4c5a-89ad-bf2aaf5d8197
2026-01-12 15:31:01.47328+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.473286+00	1f0a7524-b547-441d-9707-5166aee6a538	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Whenever I take someone's backwards rollback boat entry virginity I like to capture it for our scubafans, jajaja.   Here is Bill's first time rolling backwards off a boat.  Great job Bill!  It takes a lot of courage the first time.  Thanks Alberto for demonstrating.</p><p>Pro Tip: Next time also hold your mask with your fingers while you hold your regulator.  Excellent job on protecting your head!</p><p>As always a huge thanks to our Capitan Larry and his awesome vessel Rubia for the charter.  Having a competent captain with 28 years of diving experience and a better than most seaworthy vessel with a good reliable and fast engine makes all the difference for a safe fun dive.</p><p>Captain Larry has been my mentor helping me and my friends to learn how ocean boat diving is done right!  I can't thank him enough for helping us to become better safer divers, following our bubbles, and never losing track of where we are.</p><p>Two of my biggest fears are being struck by a propeller on the surface or being lost by the boat.  Every time we surface we can count on the Rubia safely being there waiting for us with the propeller disengaged and Larry fully aware of every diver in the water like a momma duck counting her ducklings!</p><p>-----</p><p>Cada vez que tomo la virginidad de la entrada del barco al rev\\\\u00e9s de alguien, me gusta capturarla para nuestros fan\\\\u00e1ticos del buceo, jajaja. Esta es la primera vez que Bill rueda hacia atr\\\\u00e1s desde un bote. \\\\u00a1Buen trabajo Bill! Se necesita mucho coraje la primera vez. Gracias Alberto por demostrar.</p><p>Consejo profesional: la pr\\\\u00f3xima vez sostenga tambi\\\\u00e9n la m\\\\u00e1scara con los dedos mientras sostiene el regulador. \\\\u00a1Excelente trabajo protegiendo tu cabeza!</p><p>Como siempre, muchas gracias a nuestro Capit\\\\u00e1n Larry y su impresionante barco Rubia por el alquiler. Tener un capit\\\\u00e1n competente con 28 a\\\\u00f1os de experiencia en buceo y una embarcaci\\\\u00f3n mejor que la mayor\\\\u00eda en condiciones de navegar con un buen motor confiable y r\\\\u00e1pido marca la diferencia para una inmersi\\\\u00f3n segura y divertida.</p><p>\\\\u00a1El Capit\\\\u00e1n Larry ha sido mi mentor y nos ha ayudado a m\\\\u00ed y a mis amigos a aprender c\\\\u00f3mo se hace bien el buceo en barco en el oc\\\\u00e9ano! No puedo agradecerle lo suficiente por ayudarnos a convertirnos en buceadores m\\\\u00e1s seguros, siguiendo nuestras burbujas y sin perder nunca la noci\\\\u00f3n de d\\\\u00f3nde estamos.</p><p>Dos de mis mayores temores son que me golpee una h\\\\u00e9lice en la superficie o que me pierda el barco. \\\\u00a1Cada vez que salimos a la superficie, podemos contar con que la Rubia estar\\\\u00e1 all\\\\u00ed esper\\\\u00e1ndonos con la h\\\\u00e9lice desconectada y Larry completamente consciente de cada buzo en el agua como una mam\\\\u00e1 pato contando sus patitos!</p>"}	0	t	35673bbf-651c-40c6-8d23-f91f50565f6b
2026-01-12 15:31:01.481433+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.481445+00	18fb708f-418e-439b-b019-dec4e8514464	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Looking up at some friends from the abyss.</p>"}	0	t	db952fc1-dc8d-4231-8d51-28d1f1e6dc35
2026-01-12 15:31:01.491825+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.491834+00	e4b889dd-f763-4ecc-9069-320e318182cb	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>My friend Bill is in town for a vacation.  He, Alberto and I had a really fun couple of dives including a night dive yesterday after which we met up with our other friends at a  Beach Club where Victor snapped a few awesome pics of us coming back from our dive</p>"}	0	t	697dde33-8fd8-48a9-a6b3-e5bd7709c444
2026-01-12 15:31:01.500307+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.500315+00	d71b0e17-73f7-4fda-b852-ad60d4902e1e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>My friend Bill came to visit from Phoenix and we went on a few dives with Alberto.  These guys worked on some skills for their advanced open water and nitrox certifications.  We checked out the Juan Escutia and the reef.  They mapped the wreck looking for future places to penetrate making note of hazards and depth while tracking their air and times.  They also learned some about drift diving techniques and the importance of having a DSMB and how to safely shoot the DSMB, paying special heed to how we need to avoid entanglement and an uncontrolled ascent.  We also practiced proper boat diving and surface habits and we experienced a negative entry into current.  These guys made a great buddy team and had a lot of fun in the ocean.  I can't wait to dive with them again!</p><p>---</p><p>Mi amigo Bill vino a visitarnos desde Phoenix y realizamos algunas inmersiones con Alberto. Estos muchachos trabajaron en algunas habilidades para sus certificaciones avanzadas de aguas abiertas y nitrox. Verificamos el Juan Escutia y el arrecife. Mapearon el naufragio en busca de lugares futuros para penetrar tomando nota de los peligros y la profundidad mientras rastreaban su aire y tiempos. Tambi\\\\u00e9n aprendieron algo sobre t\\\\u00e9cnicas de buceo a la deriva y la importancia de tener un DSMB y c\\\\u00f3mo disparar con seguridad el DSMB, prestando especial atenci\\\\u00f3n a c\\\\u00f3mo debemos evitar enredos y un ascenso descontrolado. Tambi\\\\u00e9n practicamos un buen buceo desde barco y h\\\\u00e1bitos de superficie y experimentamos una entrada negativa en la corriente. Estos muchachos formaron un gran equipo de amigos y se divirtieron mucho en el oc\\\\u00e9ano. \\\\u00a1No puedo esperar para bucear con ellos de nuevo!</p>"}	0	t	e8152265-6580-43c6-a9cd-86255a534017
2026-01-12 15:31:01.508903+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.508911+00	73d6032b-f338-4e54-a35f-53e73a5fc58c	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Yesterday in an underwater cave I was able to find a lost line in a zero visibility silt out, followed by both my buddy's and my primary light \\\\</p>"}	0	t	fea3fdfb-127a-4a98-86e0-1949ac15bc44
2026-01-12 15:31:01.51655+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.516557+00	75f4f95d-f85f-4f41-b476-892fee14826d	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>A cave lives therein. Let's go explore it.</p><p>Una cueva vive all\\\\u00ed. Vamos a explorarlo.</p><p>#happydiving #buceofeliz</p>"}	0	t	79e7949f-8b7f-40c4-a800-ec6bec895522
2026-01-12 15:31:01.523581+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.523592+00	4ff66207-51fa-4a99-b1f4-19790f14fdd7	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>It's been a busy couple of days as I start learning cave diving.</p>"}	0	t	6490f230-0722-4532-9ef5-fc9319b1b6ad
2026-01-12 15:31:01.537514+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.537533+00	ab5ca4d4-1f1e-46be-a2bc-c2fc5a2daea1	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>As part of the PADI wreck specialty course I'm preparing to teach I've been researching the wreck here in Puerto Morelos that is going to be my classroom.  It has a neat history and after being sold to the Mexican Navy it was renamed after one of the Ni\\\\u00f1os H\\\\u00e9roes who as legend says, wrapped himself in the Mexican flag and jumped from a cliff to prevent it from falling into the US attackers hands during The Battle of Chapultepec.</p><p>Three of these WWII minesweepers were sold to Mexico and later sunk as artificial reefs in Puerto Morelos, Cozumel and Veracruz.  The one here in Puerto Morelos is C56 Juan Escutia.  Formerly the USS Knave AM-256, an admiral class minesweeper, it is the same type of ship that was also sunk in Veracruz (USS Jubilant AM-255) and in Cozumel (still researching).</p><p>As part of the wreck course, prior to any penetration, students are taught how to survey the wreck and create a plan to identify features and possible entry points for penetration.  And to do prior research to find any plans or photos and diagrams to assist with defining primary and secondary objectives during their dive planning.  As a history buff myself, I think it's super cool to find the \\\\</p>"}	0	t	72734e7c-dd9a-407f-9299-e980d05d81a4
2026-01-12 15:31:01.551983+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.551995+00	c1b1816d-c7c7-40ff-94bc-db050546a832	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>This is a great idea and one that I'm going to incorporate into my teaching toolkit.</p><p>I also help students prevent the trigger mentioned in the article.  Those anxious nose breathers get some advice early on.   Before we even start confined water I instruct new students to practice controlling their nose breathing by filling the kitchen sink with water, submerging their face without a mask, and breathing with just a snorkle to figure it out and get used to the feeling of a little water in their nose.</p>"}	0	t	f8c20392-e886-4917-8c8b-ef9eeb208cf5
2026-01-12 15:31:01.563085+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.563098+00	95ec1b57-f657-4d95-9669-0b168ad2257f	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The 23 foot deep caves have been flooded 8000 years.</p>"}	0	t	0190380c-26ff-449b-be38-6e7210269c74
2026-01-12 15:31:01.573449+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.573458+00	35cb1d45-72c7-4585-9d9f-2d1959f7a96a	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I had a nice visit with my friends Terrena and Jim who live close to my folks in Florida.  They come to Mexico regularly and it was Terrena's birthday week vacation so they hit me up to have a nice afternoon on the beach followed by a lunch at La Caba\\\\u00f1a.  It was their first visit to the Colonia side and it was a real pleaser.  They both appreciated the authentic part of town where I live.</p><p>Jim and I went on a little shore dive for fun together and saw a lot of fish and and corals as I gave him a tour of one of my favorite dive sites.  Jim loved it and agreed it's the best shore dive he's ever done.</p><p>Where they are from in Florida on the Gulf side getting to a decent dive site is 50 miles out on a boat.  Or a drive across the peninsula to the east coast to dive in the Atlantic or down to the keys.  I'm looking forward on my next visit to my folks to hopefully take a trip to a Florida dive site and go diving again togethe soon.</p><p>Tuve una agradable visita con mis amigos Terrena y Jim que viven cerca de mis padres en Florida. Vienen a M\\\\u00e9xico con regularidad y era la semana de vacaciones del cumplea\\\\u00f1os de Terrena, as\\\\u00ed que me llamaron para pasar una agradable tarde en la playa seguida de un almuerzo en La Caba\\\\u00f1a. Era su primera visita al lado de Colonia y fue un verdadero placer. Ambos apreciaron la parte aut\\\\u00e9ntica de la ciudad donde vivo.</p><p>Jim y yo hicimos un peque\\\\u00f1o buceo en la costa para divertirnos juntos y vimos muchos peces y corales mientras le daba un recorrido por uno de mis sitios de buceo favoritos. A Jim le encant\\\\u00f3 y estuvo de acuerdo en que es la mejor inmersi\\\\u00f3n en tierra que ha hecho.</p><p>De donde son en Florida en el lado del Golfo, llegar a un sitio de buceo decente est\\\\u00e1 a 50 millas en un bote. O un paseo por la pen\\\\u00ednsula hasta la costa este para bucear en el Atl\\\\u00e1ntico o bajar a los cayos. Espero con ansias la pr\\\\u00f3xima visita a mis padres para hacer un viaje a un sitio de buceo de Florida y volver a bucear juntos pronto.</p>"}	0	t	1d863c39-3f6d-422d-ac9f-e8f7cc51b5fd
2026-01-12 15:31:01.581944+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.581952+00	acc044b7-4650-45eb-9668-b7644f794dba	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I've added some task loading today during my sidemount training by bringing my Olympus TG-6 along.</p><p>I am able to stow the long-hose now a little easier, even with one hand, so to give my mind some new focus points I brought the camera to shoot some photos of critters while also maintaining my good buoyancy and trim.</p><p>I removed the strobe and the wide angle lens to reduce the footprint of the camera and incrementally add more tasks with those items later in my training when I'm more automatic with muscle memory for managing the other skills.</p><p>I think challenges for me are a good way to learn and keep my interest but are best added incrementally in order to avoid being overwhelmed with task loading.  Having some real-world fun on long practice dives sure makes the skills homework more enjoyable.</p><p>I don't usually recommend divers add in a camera until after their skills are solid, they are familiar with the dive site, and .</p><p>I feel pretty solid with diving with 2 tanks now.  The fine motor skills and muscle memory for stowing things and getting them out, maintaining situational awareness while focusing on getting a good shot. All the while practicing good buoyancy is something I'm getting the hang of.</p>"}	0	t	a631cd0f-34c8-40b3-b2a0-989c74f8ec38
2026-01-12 15:31:01.589954+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.589962+00	a4f74cfd-3bc6-4555-8fcc-414a1f251118	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Warning if you like Apple Products and think they're awesome stop reading right here and don't leave any comments.  No matter what I say I'm not going to change your mind or be able to combat the 100's of Millions of dollars of marketing Apple has spent to market to you.  This article will just piss you off and you'll feel the brand loyalty urge you've got bubble up.  Seriously if you want to dive with an Apple watch go ahead and do it.  Save yourself the aggravation and don't read this.</p><p>------- For those who care what a guy has to say who has taken apart probabaly close to 10,000 laptops including many Apples and is a professional dive instructor, here is my opinion.  -----</p><p>I've started seeing posts in diver forums about the new Apple watch slash \\\\</p>"}	0	t	1b97d5bd-9f0b-464e-9bcc-9e4141b68f66
2026-01-12 15:31:01.693361+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.693376+00	685add1b-c41d-47db-a819-8ef855464403	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Beautiful day for shore diving Ojo De Agua.   I have 2000psi left after a 42 min dive.  I think I'll get a little tan and then go again.</p>"}	0	t	d08f0701-8ffe-4356-87a0-7cc7ec0b269f
2026-01-12 15:31:01.709861+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.709885+00	aec6050f-a209-47d8-8a4f-5b54547d33d3	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Are you interested in underwater photography?  I found this excellent discussion given by Sir Alex Mustard, one of the world's finest underwater photographers.</p><p>As a PADI specialty instructor in underwater digital imaging I can offer my students the opportunity to to get started online with the PADI e-learning materials, face to face instruction over zoom, and then go diving with you as your buddy while you practice what you've learned.</p>"}	0	t	69b65a55-8c95-495a-b2fd-b31fb6b159a6
2026-01-12 15:31:02.16701+00	2026-01-12 15:31:02.167018+00	a55b9b1f-b383-4ffc-bcbc-cefa137fabaa	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Diving.  It's like a hike right out the backdoor. To have this resource so close is amazing.  It's like living in the foothills of the Mountains.  But you take your hike underwater.</p>"}	0	t	59d2e28c-742f-4ef4-bab3-3122c303a933
2026-01-12 15:31:01.597706+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.597714+00	cf50a243-f5b5-4f12-a44b-2462b4a5aed2	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Took Alberto on a dive and we practiced some navigation skills for his PADI Advanced Open Water Diver course.</p><p>The way I'm teaching him navigation is hands on.  He's a cartographer so we're making it more interesting and broader by mapping the features and attractions of Ojo De Agua, the shore diving area in Puerto Morelos Mexico.</p><p>Our plan is for both of us to have fun while improving our underwater navigation skills while we create a scuba trail that can be used for the Navigation course for future students and others who have an interest in having a map to discover the lagoon.</p><p>We will include additional map layers from data sources from the National Park and also interactive images and videos with geotagging so people can see what fun they can have diving here.  #happydiving #buceofeliz #padiinstructor</p><p>----</p><p>Llev\\\\u00e9 a Alberto a bucear y practicamos algunas habilidades de navegaci\\\\u00f3n para su curso PADI Advanced Open Water Diver.</p><p>La forma en que le estoy ense\\\\u00f1ando a navegar es pr\\\\u00e1ctica. \\\\u00c9l es cart\\\\u00f3grafo, por lo que lo estamos haciendo m\\\\u00e1s interesante y m\\\\u00e1s amplio al mapear las caracter\\\\u00edsticas y atracciones de Ojo De Agua, el \\\\u00e1rea de buceo en la costa en Puerto Morelos, M\\\\u00e9xico.</p><p>Nuestro plan es que ambos nos divirtamos mientras mejoramos nuestras habilidades de navegaci\\\\u00f3n submarina mientras creamos un sendero de buceo que puede ser utilizado para el curso de Navegaci\\\\u00f3n para futuros estudiantes y otras personas que tengan inter\\\\u00e9s en tener un mapa para descubrir la laguna.</p><p>Incluiremos capas de mapas adicionales de fuentes de datos del Parque Nacional y tambi\\\\u00e9n im\\\\u00e1genes y videos interactivos con geoetiquetado para que las personas puedan ver qu\\\\u00e9 diversi\\\\u00f3n pueden tener buceando aqu\\\\u00ed.</p>"}	0	t	ea986399-0821-4f25-931d-95198ed5584c
2026-01-12 15:31:01.606041+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.606049+00	166f5c36-ada5-40a4-bd7a-d2c5a0f69a02	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>It's interesting getting used to the current flowing north.  As I practiced my sidemount exercises I took some breaks along the way to take some photos.  Again these are with the GoPro to make it easier without excessive task loading since I'm learning some new buoyancy skills.  I breathed the tanks all the way down to 400 PSI to learn how to manage them positively buoyant.  I'll refill them tomorrow and go diving with a friend of mine here who is another instructor who I've been promising a dive with since the last time I was here.  Enjoy!  #happydiving!</p>"}	0	t	6bdde295-3e5d-4ce8-a94b-764fd062a122
2026-01-12 15:31:01.614303+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.614311+00	8a7ae935-dab5-4f52-93dc-b30f824a5fde	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Here are a few more pictures I shot on the GoPro today in between practicing drills with sidemount.  It's actually easier to take photos with sidemount, the buoyancy is easier I think.</p>"}	0	t	c382da4e-0ad6-4bc7-9e3f-ac7171fb1004
2026-01-12 15:31:01.621479+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.621486+00	b863357c-8ec5-45b1-9292-7442bee0e327	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Today was my first sidemount class as I prepare for my full cave course.  It was super awesome diving in the cenote today  The buoyancy is a little different with sidemount.  My homework is to dive sidemount everyday in Ojo De Agua until the class starts so I can perfect the skills I learned today.   If anyone wants to dive with me and watch me practice  I'll be happy to guide you.</p>"}	0	t	24f3af3f-b3a3-4575-b2b0-25e637dfd247
2026-01-12 15:31:01.628809+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.628817+00	a791b290-6bd8-45c5-9378-96bae7b8628f	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Sidemount practice today.  Let me just say I love this way of diving.  The buoyancy and trim was not too hard to learn and once I did it's much easier on my back then back mount.  The maneuverability is much better.  And as far as effort needed for moving the tanks and the gear from the taxi to the beach goes it's almost on par with diving a backplate and wing with weights and all the things in terms of weight and is I'd say it's just as much weight to carry when I bring a pony.  Also my shoulders feel a lot better from not carrying a tank on my back.  A bonus of course is the redundancy and self-reliant safety that you get and of course the time underwater is doubled on this particular shore dive when deco isn't really a concern.  Full cave cert course starts 9/20.</p>"}	0	t	5c7e0e4c-a783-4404-b9bb-dcd2c0280079
2026-01-12 15:31:01.636536+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.636544+00	ba85a7d7-9c6f-4c20-8401-ec5c1ae25bc2	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Today is a sidemount training day in a Cenote.  Looking forward to training hard on my way to becoming a full cave trainee candidate.</p><p>Much thanks to my instructor and PADI course director Angel Navarro Moya with The Go Pro Family in Playa Del Carmen for giving me this opportunity and believing in me.</p>"}	0	t	30fe7312-b74b-45de-8fd8-31a372249522
2026-01-12 15:31:01.643946+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.643953+00	bbca4231-edba-430e-875e-3f6d8695ec6e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Sin tocar nada!  The end of my snorkel tour briefing.  Let's stick together.  If you need help or get tired let me know and I will pull you with the buoy.</p>"}	0	t	492c4d73-aab1-4eb9-a26e-131fca302598
2026-01-12 15:31:01.651683+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.651691+00	b708604f-3e6c-438a-a30f-7d4d2d58494b	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I took my first real snorkel tour with Alberto and his 7 cousins last Saturday.  They were here visiting from Mexico City.  Captain Larry took us to the Rodman site for the tour and assisted me with learning the route at this tour site.</p><p>I really appreciate how much training Larry  has given me the many times I've been on his boat.   He also taught me how to tie off the boat to the buoy and to the pier.  So I feel like I\\\\</p>"}	0	t	c2c6cbae-5357-4d44-8339-ea90e2294b60
2026-01-12 15:31:01.659919+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.659927+00	da9bb038-df2f-453e-9b87-6ef6a41f2d4c	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Who wants to be my dive buddy?</p><p>If anyone is interested in diving 2 shallow reef sites Wednesday I think mid morning/early afternoon? There is room on a boat for 1 more diver.  It's for a good price of 1000 pesos payable to the operator.</p><p>I'll go with you as your buddy. Especially if you want to get your enriched air (NITROX) cert.  If you've never dived before and have always wanted to try it, and are fit to dive with strong swimming skills, I'll be happy to donate my time and teach you the PADI Discover Scuba Diving course or we can start learning the full open water beforehand (You have to buy the PADI course materials). \\n \\nI'm a PADI instructor in teaching status and am a credentialed guide for the national park. I'm trying to share my love of diving and make new friends who are interested in the amazing resource here.   I'm also an enriched air (NITROX) specialty instructor. If you buy the PADI E-learning, I'll waive the instructor fee during the dives.</p><p>What's the catch?  I am working towards my Master Scuba Diver Trainer and need the experience and student certifications to finish.  So you'll need to be as patient with me as I am with you \\\\ud83d\\\\ude42</p><p>This isn't the only opportunity, so feel free to message me even if you can't go this week but are interested the next time we're trying to fill a boat.</p>"}	0	t	9eef44c8-c60c-4870-970f-497a667aeedb
2026-01-12 15:31:01.667353+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.667361+00	894f0b62-c2d7-4d7a-a9fa-fe6cd74fbb17	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Not the best conditions today but the water sure felt nice and it's always great exercise and an opportunity to keep learning more about the camera and using the strobe.</p>"}	0	t	93d7d94d-4a2c-4f88-ae1c-b4cb4358b466
2026-01-12 15:31:01.677835+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.677849+00	bc4ecd2a-71eb-4e80-8b2d-ab8e2ad7351e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I went on a couple shore dives today and have started practicing with my new camera.  This is pretty sub par underwater photography, but we all have to start someplace!  I am looking forward to mastering the settings and use of the strobe.</p>"}	0	t	0714f6f0-c9ba-42a6-9451-6032fca86c3c
2026-01-12 15:31:01.879522+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.879531+00	d9123c7c-b912-4d30-97fe-43bafe5e49b5	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Happiness can be living  life at your own risk in familiar places.</p>"}	0	t	b268d087-4430-40b2-82f3-ffe693d7164e
2026-01-12 15:31:01.726856+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.726873+00	ec8be7cd-ab43-4c21-a12a-911045ba5894	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>I really enjoy teaching confined water courses when I'm home in St Louis.  Especially one on one with excellent and eager private students.</p><p>I'm super proud of Sara who is ready for her open water checkout dives she will experience in the warm ocean on her honeymoon.</p><p>I get so much satisfaction knowing I've played a part helping to make a magical tropical moment more special and memorable.</p><p>While the Midwestern pool pales in comparison with the reef, being that first instructor responsible for teaching the foundational water skills, brings me joy knowing I've  prepared a new diver for a lifelong pursuit of happy diving.</p>"}	0	t	5c3a0098-7b4c-47bc-aeb2-cf4eeab91ef1
2026-01-12 15:31:01.737334+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.737343+00	18d9aaad-7195-401e-9f0c-0b7e966894fd	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>One of my favorite dives is from the shore in Ojo De Agua. Here I am just hanging out with this school of Atlantic Spadefish which, has grown quite a bit since I started diving with them. If you've snorkled and seen these fish from above, here is what it's like under the surface.</p><p>Once I find them I calmly and patiently hang out breathing deeply and super slow trying to make my bubbles as quite as I can until they let me join their school and then take my time floating along with them weightlessly.</p><p>For those who are curious I shot this with a GoPro 9 and changed the angle of the lens settings (narrower/slight zoom) to improve the focus, details, and bring the subjects closer.</p>"}	0	t	d4bd1a7e-ec28-46f1-8e8a-1deedd570dd9
2026-01-12 15:31:01.745296+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.745302+00	108cc846-19b8-4809-b495-3e2ec40a65ae	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>There were so many Atlantic spadefish today during my dive.</p>"}	0	t	35d89176-8f2c-45c5-9784-fe3be5ed11ad
2026-01-12 15:31:01.752785+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.752793+00	01dc299a-0b8a-4790-b29d-69d1653f86ed	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Puffers are so cool.  This one was super curious swimming with me today.</p>"}	0	t	f9451370-56bb-403b-b59b-50fd5c86add0
