2026-01-12 15:31:01.918726+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.918734+00	8b24d7cd-92fc-4a82-b6c8-52ef13bf850d	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>The idea of insuring the reef to assure rapid funding for disaster recovery of the ecosystem is a first here in Mexico.  Wow!</p>"}	0	t	c9186d4c-611a-4426-9dbe-ee66b2572d43
2026-01-12 15:31:01.926331+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.926338+00	6cdc0f2b-d4ae-4806-96ba-928d8e51cc67	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Can you guess what's happening today?</p>"}	0	t	cd68a98b-980b-48da-950d-5528842c24a7
2026-01-12 15:31:01.933871+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.933878+00	e5a63dc1-bcbe-4d8a-9094-9d6237884fc4	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>So interesting</p><p>All clownfish are born male.</p><p>There\\\\u2019s a good reason why both main characters in Finding Nemo are male, at least initially. All clownfish are born that way, and it\\\\u2019s only when a group\\\\u2019s dominant female dies or disappears that a male will develop into a female and become the new matriarch. All clownfish have the ability to turn female, and the change is permanent once it occurs. The transformation begins almost immediately after the dominant female leaves, and starts in the brain before manifesting itself in the sex organs. Had the beloved Pixar film been devoted to scientific accuracy, Nemo\\\\u2019s father, Marlin, might not have been just his sole caregiver after tragedy befalls the boy\\\\u2019s mother \\\\u2014 he might literally have become his mother.</p><p>Clownfish aren\\\\u2019t the only reef-dwellers that can change sex. The bluehead wrasse does it as well, only in reverse: When a dominant male leaves its group, the largest female transforms into a male over the course of just 21 days. Researchers have identified no fewer than 500 fish species capable of changing sex; some, like the coral-dwelling species of gobies, can even switch back and forth. The process is believed to have reproductive benefits, as it allows a single fish to reproduce as both sexes throughout its life.</p>"}	0	t	6848af55-47de-462d-b51e-171e689c65a8
2026-01-12 15:31:01.94138+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.941388+00	716ce9a3-0c7a-4558-ab6a-3f58c868f7a5	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>We had a great dive so glad to be able to share JaNola's pictures</p>"}	0	t	481840a8-6fc1-4afd-a283-13ddc713c3c4
2026-01-12 15:31:01.949159+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.949171+00	80c93033-fa7b-4116-b183-7413493b7f0b	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>We had a great dive so glad to be able to share JaNola's pictures</p>"}	0	t	4b7b76dc-7153-4744-872d-4824874ce82e
2026-01-12 15:31:01.956538+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.956546+00	26ce0005-e865-42de-9eea-2184878cc456	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>JaNola, Jairo, and I went to the shipwreck last Monday.  We were greeted by a ray that was a bit curious about us.</p><p>Thanks to our guide Jairo and King Scuba and Captain Larry.</p>"}	0	t	e002c355-28d3-42f5-81a3-bfc215fefdc0
2026-01-12 15:31:01.963797+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.963805+00	36b0ebcd-4d1d-464f-916b-447b19c4c89a	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>We went on a Reef Dive after the shipwreck.  Victor brought his camera.  You can see how the water changes the color of the light with the flash. Cynthia and Angie, , and I had a very relaxing dive.</p><p>Thanks again to our guide Ramiro and our Captain, Larry.</p>"}	0	t	be840e5c-ecb6-4664-a4c2-beed4e7cd416
2026-01-12 15:31:01.97094+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.970948+00	f8634da2-e7ff-4206-afd7-afcc2e0aecf7	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Happy Birthday Alberto!  Here are the photos from our dive today.  We saw a lot of fish.  And this huge moray eel that was exposed head to tail.  And we saw lots of barracudas, angelfish, etc etc etc... so many fish today.</p><p>And I'm happy to report that I did not run into any lines or see any damage done to the reef despite the report of people poaching in the park.</p><p>Aqua-adventure was a success!!  We searched the entire area assigned.  67 minute single tank dive with plenty of no deco time left because this is such a shallow dive site.  It's like the equivalent of a hike in the foothills of our backyard.  We're so lucky to have this so accessible here. This is one of my favorite spots to dive and just relax.</p><p>#gaydivebuddy #padiinstructor #projectaware #happybirthdayalberto</p>"}	0	t	353c836e-548c-4488-8941-fae1cf59c967
2026-01-12 15:31:01.978216+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.978224+00	bb397584-e96b-44dd-a3cb-39faa56a572e	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>My scuba sense has detected that today's dive must include a volunteer aqua-mission to investigate possible damage done by people who brought line and a harpoon to illegally fish last night in the park.</p><p>Spear fishing is forbidden as it not only causes damage to the natural fish population, it also makes them fearful of and less enjoyable for future humans.  And can also damage corals.   Today I have been asked to volunteer to go find evidence of lines, etc..., and document and report my findings.</p><p>This aqua-mission will be a perfect addition to the regularly scheduled dive with my friend Alberto.  His birthday is coming up so what better way to celebrate with him than by going on a dive together.  Happy Birthday Alberto!!!\\n#happybirthdayalberto #gaydivebuddy #happydiving #projectaware #padiinstructor</p>"}	0	t	7cfd0c55-2c3a-4002-b791-69ae63d87f83
2026-01-12 15:31:01.985429+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.985436+00	e257bb0b-cf7b-4c75-a6b4-6a37faa2f5e2	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Last weekend Ramiro took a group of my friends and I to dive.  We explored the shipwreck and saw a lot of cool fish and corals.</p><p>The visibility was not so great so it felt really spooky on this dive.  I really loved it I love diving the shipwreck. Everyone was in awe as is normal.  Every time for me I\\\\</p>"}	0	t	b3fba00c-f375-41b1-b8f7-b247fc5d0047
2026-01-12 15:31:01.992563+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.992571+00	d3419881-d204-4164-8cfc-9024c2343f94	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Can you see it?  This is why even when things look like rocks you shouldn't touch them or hold onto them when taking photos.</p><p>The Caribbean Reef Scorpionfish is one of the more venomous creatures we dive around.</p>"}	0	t	588aab4a-c122-43d1-817f-fb5193ebbac4
2026-01-12 15:31:02.151918+00	2026-01-12 15:31:02.151925+00	ba378dd4-6658-48e3-97e2-a2e719de4d08	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Current Latitude: very nice views</p>"}	0	t	090746cf-d2c1-47ec-b249-9d94086119ff
2026-01-12 15:31:02.159527+00	2026-01-12 15:31:02.159536+00	81399432-da61-44e4-a030-14084a733792	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Another fantastic dive experience with a couple friends.  We chartered a boat and a guide and off we went!</p>"}	0	t	0b42099d-41d9-4ed4-87c5-e2470c273f9e
2026-01-12 15:31:01.999348+00	2026-01-12 15:31:01.999355+00	0d29a0f0-53c6-437e-bd0b-79d9c9822674	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>My heart breaks for captive dolphins.  Just recently In Cozumel a woman broke her spine attending a swim with dolphins once in a lifetime experience.  The cruise ship tourist industry fuels this cruelty.  They don't like being forced to perform or starve.  You wouldn't either.  Think twice before you participate in these types of tourist attractions.  Maybe take up scuba diving and be a calm passive observer, touching nothing, taking only photos, leaving only bubbles.\\nhttps://www.dolphinproject.com/campaigns/captivity-industry/swimming-with-dolphins/?fbclid=IwAR3akkoRPznQEUc1c9lofrLnUfNjcfMkPp8kxS55zqrHfhdmuaVHc42VQjg</p>"}	0	t	f600ca8e-731a-4cfb-8f39-b0bde067e95a
2026-01-12 15:31:02.006461+00	2026-01-12 15:31:02.006469+00	e0b616bd-0327-4b69-bd9b-143dce296e0d	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Check out the new QTDC sticker. Come to Launch to get one! Big thanks to Loren Bruton for making it.</p>"}	0	t	d49acada-6ae5-46a8-bc19-4c7932196c07
2026-01-12 15:31:02.013151+00	2026-01-12 15:31:02.01316+00	7947739f-d36a-4343-8c8d-f2ad404a210b	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Adult Angel at 23 meters at a shipwreck.</p><p>French Angelfish\\nScientific Name: Pomacanthus paru\\nSynonyms: Chaetodon paru\\nFamily: Pomacanthidae\\nCategory: Angelfishes\\nSize: 10 to 14 in. (25 to 35 cm)  \\nDepth: 15-80 ft. (5-25 m)\\nDistribution: Caribbean, Bahamas, Florida, Gulf of Mexico, Brazil</p>"}	0	t	c5feabf1-3440-4b13-9a50-548f7c6888f7
2026-01-12 15:31:02.020282+00	2026-01-12 15:31:02.020289+00	a1d8fff4-4ab5-44bd-b170-de459a32b057	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>So apparently I'm living in the cenote capital of the world.  Gotta start thinking about that full cave course....</p><p>With so many amazing cave divers and instructors in this area this will be the best place to learn.</p>"}	0	t	12a5b9d0-bd39-492e-9a30-ddf656093aa5
2026-01-12 15:31:02.026916+00	2026-01-12 15:31:02.026924+00	ed5a124d-e2f3-4e32-8d36-3ae0abab58f2	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Here is a little preview of the spotted eagle rays we saw today at the wreck.  I'll post the photos as soon as I get some time to pick through them and process them.  But what an amazing dive my JaNola, Jairo and I had today.  Much thanks to King Scuba and Captain Larry for managing the logistics of our dive! #gaydivebuddy #happydiving #padi #projectaware</p>"}	0	t	e8d0e300-f28e-4f36-bbed-6ca8544a09ae
2026-01-12 15:31:02.034403+00	2026-01-12 15:31:02.034412+00	34fdc6cc-b459-4c08-a416-804f81d814f1	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>My friend JaNola is in town from St. Louis and we went on our first of several dives together.  Normally she dives with Ykiki Divers in St. Louis but when she visits Mexico we always have such a blast.</p><p>Here we went on a very shallow dive to practice our buoyancy together.  The shallower the water the harder it is so when we go into deeper water and the wreck this week we're ready with better skills.</p><p>Even though this dive location is super shallow there were lots of fish and coral to see.</p>"}	0	t	d428d371-b9cb-4f61-80f1-0cd20359537e
