2026-01-12 15:31:02.173709+00	2026-01-12 15:31:02.173717+00	38419ccf-c619-4e60-8abc-8ab8bb9c26a7	\N	rich_text	{"content": "<p>Shared this in a comment, but want to make it available to all. In this shared photo you can see our essential ingredient to our reefs health and the sustainability of our marine environment. It's called seagrass, and yes it is a true plant. The darker colored sections reveal it's presence. Without it, our whole system will collapse. It is not sargassum, that is an algea created off the coast of south america, and should not be confused. Seagrass is essential to prevent beach erosion, yes it washes up on shore and stabilizes the beach sand, its roots protect the shore from storms. Along with providing food and shelter for many of our marine species. These areas need to be maintained, shore and sea,  and for the interest of all, protected . Hope this is helpful information. Enjoy this glorious day</p>"}	0	t	f78f9c89-9cf3-4a60-bca3-a433b80ce05d
