2026-01-12 15:31:00.391076+00	2026-01-12 15:37:22.670547+00	a05e40e6-f414-4079-9290-68c7c80eefa0	\N	2024-05-30-shoot-the-dsmb-to-make-a	Shoot the dsmb to make a shotline teaching aid.	published	public	[]	[]	Shoot the dsmb to make a shotline teaching aid.	Shoot the dsmb to make a shotline teaching aid. After I put the shot in place with my DSMB Buoy as a lift device instead of relying on a BCD worn by...			index, follow	{"meta": {"path": "/2024-05-30-shoot-the-dsmb-to-make-a/", "slug": "2024-05-30-shoot-the-dsmb-to-make-a", "title": "Shoot the dsmb to make a shotline teaching aid.", "robots": "index, follow", "seo_title": "Shoot the dsmb to make a shotline teaching aid.", "og_image_url": "", "seo_description": "Shoot the dsmb to make a shotline teaching aid. After I put the shot in place with my DSMB Buoy as a lift device instead of relying on a BCD worn by..."}, "blocks": [{"id": "99393fd9-dce4-4c8e-bd18-5e5333102ba1", "data": {"content": "<p>Shoot the dsmb to make a shotline teaching aid.</p><p>After I put the shot in place with my DSMB Buoy as a lift device instead of relying on a BCD worn by the diver.  I think this is a safer way to transport the weights especially when there is no BCD worn by the diver like in this instance.</p><p>In my demonstration I'm practicing in shallow water without a BCD to learn to separate my own buoyancy with that of the heavy object.</p><p>After reaching the practice spot in the sand near the shore I let some gas out of the buoy to make it manageable.  Then I attach the line and the spool.  If you notice the line has a couple loops one for a handle and a nice place for my clip, and another larger loop that allows the spool to pass through it to secure it to the buoy.</p><p>I take the buoy and the spool in my left hand and try in one smooth movement while swimming it down to maintain control of my depth i orally inflate and quickly release it before it affects my ability to stay down.  After I shoot the DSMB I clip off the line to th