2026-01-12 15:30:59.967681+00	2026-01-12 15:37:22.733377+00	9bd5769e-c90e-492e-a8d7-e08ce8968453	\N	2024-12-14-espau00f1ol-abajo-less-dangly-dos-but	Espa\\u00f1ol abajo. 	published	public	[]	[]	Espa\\u00f1ol abajo. 	Espa\\u00f1ol abajo.  Less dangly do's but without a hose I lose one less signal to inform me about my air pressure. I don't trust mechanical SPGs...			index, follow	{"meta": {"path": "/2024-12-14-espau00f1ol-abajo-less-dangly-dos-but/", "slug": "2024-12-14-espau00f1ol-abajo-less-dangly-dos-but", "title": "Espa\\\\u00f1ol abajo. ", "robots": "index, follow", "seo_title": "Espa\\\\u00f1ol abajo. ", "og_image_url": "", "seo_description": "Espa\\\\u00f1ol abajo.  Less dangly do's but without a hose I lose one less signal to inform me about my air pressure. I don't trust mechanical SPGs..."}, "blocks": [{"id": "a9e4e1d2-07cf-450c-9be8-8859de6b228c", "data": {"content": "<p>Espa\\\\u00f1ol abajo.</p><p>Less dangly do's but without a hose I lose one less signal to inform me about my air pressure.</p><p>I don't trust mechanical SPGs completely either.  I'm putting the post of the transmitter directly into the regulator I prefer to use for monkey diving from the shore .</p><p>I'll still have the feedback from the change in tank buoyancy during the dive to know when it's time to go up but normally I'd also have a high pressure hose I could feel turgidity to approximate the remaining pressure.</p><p>This does reduce a point of failure although a leaking or busted HP hose is very slow to drain a tank so not as much of a concern.  However I did buy some cheaper braided hoses and I had one die after about 50 dives. That was disappointing.</p><p>There's only one HP port on this reg so let's hope the transmitter works as planned.  On my Apeks regs I have a second HP port that I think mght be a great spot for a mini button SPG to have as a backup if the transmitter fails.  Eliminating the need for a hose.  If I had that I may be willing to forego the tactile signal I get from the HP hose.  But that skill is one I'd prefer to keep so we will see what the final configuration will be.  Of course there's no such thing as final configuration.  That's what makes the equipment part of diving part of the attraction.</p><p>----</p><p>Menos accesorios colgantes, pero sin una manguera pierdo una se\\\\u00f1al menos para informarme sobre la presi\\\\u00f3n de mi aire.</p><p>Tampoco conf\\\\u00edo completamente en los man\\\\u00f3metros mec\\\\u00e1nicos (SPG). Estoy colocando el transmisor directamente en el regulador que prefiero usar para buceo \\\\</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 0}], "version": 1, "checksum": "9376830ef8646c477380d252c23277adecc4c1f218de42c30e535e3b325ded5c", "published_at": "2026-01-12T15:30:59.972833+00:00", "access_control": {"level": "public", "required_roles": [], "required_entitlements": []}, "published_by_id": "1"}	2026-01-12 15:30:59.972833+00	0	t	default	{"source": "facebook", "original_date": "2024-12-14"}	1	70c922aa-9fcb-4b5e-8736-e82206cf5c37	Espa\\u00f1ol abajo.  Less dangly do's but without a hose I lose one less signal to inform me about my air pressure. I don't trust mechanical SPGs completely either. I'm putting the post of the...	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/485796733_1036319901848206_372768972089622954_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_s720x720_tt6&_nc_cat=100&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=127cfc&_nc_ohc=otpSHdj8W8QQ7kNvwFjETlo&_nc_oc=AdliNR2WCHS7rpJlhLVLf25frK4O-kv2MTYPieiUBMEfDG3DveulXyYa2C6PW0ZSKtw&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fcun1-1.fna&_nc_gid=Z0aT5xCzOugJ7IIe64gMsw&oh=00_AfqwuSLLL5N79hZaSb2y9Bnt4eLkrouratuHJGHxOA0RgA&oe=696AC13F	post	1	["facebook-import", "buceo-feliz"]	1ebb6e5c-53b0-41b9-b643-fb7823358e35
