2026-01-12 15:31:00.909262+00	2026-01-12 15:37:22.592775+00	a3b1516d-e35a-4112-82f1-5239cb19be5f	\N	2023-03-08-after-losing-a-camera-again-with	After losing a camera (again) with a double-ender I've changed to a...	published	public	[]	[]	After losing a camera (again) with a double-ender I've changed to a...	After losing a camera (again) with a double-ender I've changed to a boltsnap which is what I should have done and I knew I should have in the...			index, follow	{"meta": {"path": "/2023-03-08-after-losing-a-camera-again-with/", "slug": "2023-03-08-after-losing-a-camera-again-with", "title": "After losing a camera (again) with a double-ender I've changed to a...", "robots": "index, follow", "seo_title": "After losing a camera (again) with a double-ender I've changed to a...", "og_image_url": "", "seo_description": "After losing a camera (again) with a double-ender I've changed to a boltsnap which is what I should have done and I knew I should have in the..."}, "blocks": [{"id": "3df7dde1-5837-436b-be30-6e7325a96e95", "data": {"content": "<p>After losing a camera (again) with a double-ender I've changed to a boltsnap which is what I should have done and I knew I should have in the beginning.  But I didn't have an extra boltsnap yet.</p><p>Also using a double-ender was also breaking one of the rules of safe rigging which is never have a metal to metal connection due to entanglement and being unable to cut free the stuck connection.</p><p>I'm 2 for 2 though.  I was able to go back down and find them.  But I think it's time to stop pushing my luck.  I'm phasing out as many double-ender as I can.  Aside from being necessary with finger spools for dsmbs and jumps in cave navigation,, and (arguably ineffective) for tapping a tank to get someone's attention, double-enders are an untrustworthy and potentially dangerous crutch.</p><p>I use line instead of zip ties because zip ties while strong against direct forces they  easily break with twisting/sheering forces.</p><p>I learned how to tie boltsnaps starting here.  https://youtu.be/Qm_oZTAqE04</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 0}], "version": 1, "checksum": "fb1cc4e4a997140bc5d093d99f0d7ef90b3b01d4e457dbfa7830c483ece1549a", "published_at": "2026-01-12T15:31:00.913726+00:00", "access_control": {"level": "public", "required_roles": [], "required_entitlements": []}, "published_by_id": "1"}	2026-01-12 15:31:00.913726+00	0	t	default	{"source": "facebook", "original_date": "2023-03-08"}	1	70c922aa-9fcb-4b5e-8736-e82206cf5c37	After losing a camera (again) with a double-ender I've changed to a boltsnap which is what I should have done and I knew I should have in the beginning. But I didn't have an extra boltsnap yet....	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/480347813_1011539974326199_1971937100012773106_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_s720x720_tt6&_nc_cat=108&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=127cfc&_nc_ohc=FGjAqkz0G2wQ7kNvwE-Y9cM&_nc_oc=AdkEsnXqNvh2SFQOMepKOWO-SKmUlfkO17mMoX6hq9_yE8-xtWkS3lJaDs5ETAmMGHY&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fcun1-1.fna&_nc_gid=c0wbWPO8cf0dHcKrzZZb9w&oh=00_AfopNo6ZWGCuKTccPpAqzBPCk4MlLvfMKhICTspygBY0Rw&oe=696AE8B9	post	1	["facebook-import", "buceo-feliz"]	4b2ed9e6-5050-4544-ac4a-cf4f2c8ac7bb
