2026-01-12 15:31:01.162137+00	2026-01-12 15:37:22.529574+00	005993f1-a0fd-4efa-803b-2537df44f97a	\N	2023-01-06-sea-anenome-diptic-up-close-and	Sea Anenome Diptic.  Up close and personal.  Their venom is super c...	published	public	[]	[]	Sea Anenome Diptic.  Up close and personal.  Their venom is super c...	Sea Anenome Diptic. Up close and personal. Their venom is super complex with at least 17 different molecules. While most human envenomations are...			index, follow	{"meta": {"path": "/2023-01-06-sea-anenome-diptic-up-close-and/", "slug": "2023-01-06-sea-anenome-diptic-up-close-and", "title": "Sea Anenome Diptic.  Up close and personal.  Their venom is super c...", "robots": "index, follow", "seo_title": "Sea Anenome Diptic.  Up close and personal.  Their venom is super c...", "og_image_url": "", "seo_description": "Sea Anenome Diptic. Up close and personal. Their venom is super complex with at least 17 different molecules. While most human envenomations are..."}, "blocks": [{"id": "43f03f24-667d-4a76-9f31-3b0f4538748f", "data": {"content": "<p>Sea Anenome Diptic.  Up close and personal.  Their venom is super complex with at least 17 different molecules.  While most human envenomations are harmless they can cause a pruritic rash.  But to their prey the venom is deadly.  There are two different types of cells that produce the toxins.</p><p>Nematocytes that shoot little barbs and trigger a venom release upon contact are the same type of cell found in jellyfish and fire corals.  And then there are these other weird cells, ectodermal gland cells that release a toxin into the water that also assists with disabling and catching prey.</p><p>The reason why sea anemone toxins are located in two different types of cells remains unknown. However, secretion by gland cells may allow for delivery of larger amounts of the toxin, and present an opportunity to extend the reach of venom use by the anemone beyond direct contact.</p><p>https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6627431/</p><p>--</p><p>D\\\\u00edptico de an\\\\u00e9mona de mar. De cerca y personal. Su veneno es s\\\\u00faper complejo con al menos 17 mol\\\\u00e9culas diferentes. Si bien la mayor\\\\u00eda de los envenenamientos humanos son inofensivos, pueden causar un sarpullido pruriginoso. Pero para su presa el veneno es mortal. Hay dos tipos diferentes de c\\\\u00e9lulas que producen las toxinas.</p><p>Los nematocitos que disparan peque\\\\u00f1as p\\\\u00faas y desencadenan la liberaci\\\\u00f3n de veneno al contacto son el mismo tipo de c\\\\u00e9lula que se encuentra en las medusas y los corales de fuego. Y luego est\\\\u00e1n estas otras c\\\\u00e9lulas extra\\\\u00f1as, la c\\\\u00e9lula de la gl\\\\u00e1ndula ectod\\\\u00e9rmica que libera una toxina en el agua que tambi\\\\u00e9n ayuda a inhabilitar y atrapar presas.</p><p>Se desconoce la raz\\\\u00f3n por la que las toxinas de las an\\\\u00e9monas de mar se encuentran en dos tipos diferentes de c\\\\u00e9lulas. Sin embargo, la secreci\\\\u00f3n de las c\\\\u00e9lulas glandulares puede permitir el suministro de mayores cantidades de la toxina y presentar una oportunidad para extender el alcance del uso del veneno por parte de la an\\\\u00e9mona m\\\\u00e1s all\\\\u00e1 del contacto directo.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 0}], "version": 1, "checksum": "0197b362669abb8f183e7c1dce2d2c8dd415ea64f16ca9b593fd61051733695f", "published_at": "2026-01-12T15:31:01.167206+00:00", "access_control": {"level": "public", "required_roles": [], "required_entitlements": []}, "published_by_id": "1"}	2026-01-12 15:31:01.167206+00	0	t	default	{"source": "facebook", "original_date": "2023-01-06"}	1	70c922aa-9fcb-4b5e-8736-e82206cf5c37	Sea Anenome Diptic. Up close and personal. Their venom is super complex with at least 17 different molecules. While most human envenomations are harmless they can cause a pruritic rash. But to...	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/469543014_902765781840394_3912992997302603046_n.jpg