mosos.</p><p>Son dif\\\\u00edciles de fotografiar porque son muy t\\\\u00edmidos y se alejan r\\\\u00e1pidamente. Me ha resultado \\\\u00fatil quedarme en un lugar y esperar a que vengan y empiecen a ser un poco curiosos. Se necesita mucha paciencia.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 0}], "version": 1, "checksum": "0369dbd9e14263856e9a0624579c5561f04efc747c00a19f293101b447a56cce", "published_at": "2026-01-12T15:31:01.207411+00:00", "access_control": {"level": "public", "required_roles": [], "required_entitlements": []}, "published_by_id": "1"}	2026-01-12 15:31:01.207411+00	0	t	default	{"source": "facebook", "original_date": "2023-01-04"}	1	70c922aa-9fcb-4b5e-8736-e82206cf5c37	I went diving a couple days ago and have started practicing more macro underwater photography with small fish like this Carribbean Sharpnose Puffer. When you see them in the water they are about...	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/484994196_1036056521874544_838402136856210603_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_s590x590_tt6&_nc_cat=101&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=127cfc&_nc_ohc=vujX_AuEbJQQ7kNvwFYvHDI&_nc_oc=Adl8Wbg0zdmD3bH04ycdKqA-ruZaOMVTYa4uyUlLmWICuSxoXKFfZLdEax_9jR9Wr0A&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fcun1-1.fna&_nc_gid=p_6EZodhRF3Ros5wgLYC0g&oh=00_AfrsIYbCdqF7aOwSjb-M0ElZxyuyENYrTmU3lMpjU1sSMA&oe=696AC70E	post	1	["facebook-import", "buceo-feliz"]	a636e24e-7b15-4b60-8a1a-0d8bd495bd34
