2026-01-12 15:31:01.931926+00	2026-01-12 15:37:22.339239+00	6848af55-47de-462d-b51e-171e689c65a8	\N	2022-05-13-so-interesting-all-clownfish-are-born	So interesting	published	public	[]	[]	So interesting	So interesting All clownfish are born male. There\\u2019s a good reason why both main characters in Finding Nemo are male, at least initially. All...			index, follow	{"meta": {"path": "/2022-05-13-so-interesting-all-clownfish-are-born/", "slug": "2022-05-13-so-interesting-all-clownfish-are-born", "title": "So interesting", "robots": "index, follow", "seo_title": "So interesting", "og_image_url": "", "seo_description": "So interesting All clownfish are born male. There\\\\u2019s a good reason why both main characters in Finding Nemo are male, at least initially. All..."}, "blocks": [{"id": "e5a63dc1-bcbe-4d8a-9094-9d6237884fc4", "data": {"content": "<p>So interesting</p><p>All clownfish are born male.</p><p>There\\\\u2019s a good reason why both main characters in Finding Nemo are male, at least initially. All clownfish are born that way, and it\\\\u2019s only when a group\\\\u2019s dominant female dies or disappears that a male will develop into a female and become the new matriarch. All clownfish have the ability to turn female, and the change is permanent once it occurs. The transformation begins almost immediately after the dominant female leaves, and starts in the brain before manifesting itself in the sex organs. Had the beloved Pixar film been devoted to scientific accuracy, Nemo\\\\u2019s father, Marlin, might not have been just his sole caregiver after tragedy befalls the boy\\\\u2019s mother \\\\u2014 he might literally have become his mother.</p><p>Clownfish aren\\\\u2019t the only reef-dwellers that can change sex. The bluehead wrasse does it as well, only in reverse: When a dominant male leaves its group, the largest female transforms into a male over the course of just 21 days. Researchers have identified no fewer than 500 fish species capable of changing sex; some, like the coral-dwelling species of gobies, can even switch back and forth. The process is believed to have reproductive benefits, as it allows a single fish to reproduce as both sexes throughout its life.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 0}], "version": 1, "checksum": "42c675b104b77c8c57f9950aff173754819abd75bcbab70c604ae862531ab32e", "published_at": "2026-01-12T15:31:01.936640+00:00", "access_control": {"level": "public", "required_roles": [], "required_entitlements": []}, "published_by_id": "1"}	2026-01-12 15:31:01.93664+00	0	t	default	{"source": "facebook", "original_date": "2022-05-13"}	1	70c922aa-9fcb-4b5e-8736-e82206cf5c37	So interesting All clownfish are born male. There\\u2019s a good reason why both main characters in Finding Nemo are male, at least initially. All clownfish are born that way, and it\\u2019s only...	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/482128655_1021806936632836_9072761962803235165_n.jpg?_nc_cat=104&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=833d8c&_nc_ohc=x4NrUoM0YdgQ7kNvwHC3kMy&_nc_oc=Adn3MaGQOnD9Lb9yYeXqlqZ9eASxGpPax6ov2OxASdY1QLst778DUFpH4CYqx0WLaqI&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fcun1-1.fna&_nc_gid=dpy7mcjLyP7IU4J8J5CWAQ&oh=00_AfpzOUonWxLdJj3dPosCV0jBSFft2dK98syFExIIOZhwNw&oe=696AC1E4	post	1	["facebook-import", "buceo-feliz"]	1ebb6e5c-53b0-41b9-b643-fb7823358e35
