ept in the ocean. The ocean is 5 minutes from my house here in the...	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t15.5256-10/319534373_3316311405249498_8551883651418580800_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_s960x960_tt6&_nc_cat=108&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=54741f&_nc_ohc=-T1zycd928AQ7kNvwGNjcO4&_nc_oc=AdlA6IyGEyhHi-Q0po84gkzTNBldyY-gR9B-IFRZzD4oa61FUuKeNCmj7CX1lm3Ltfw&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fcun1-1.fna&_nc_gid=EDsNdBl78wOSGQO_PWHAiA&oh=00_AfqFtPt5qOX3HlNrVhkd2wji5Jbex8ufgbIEKq_BgsAKNg&oe=696AF5C1	post	1	["facebook-import", "buceo-feliz"]	99de6173-8156-47ad-b4fa-e64b01814a44
2026-01-12 15:31:01.852824+00	2026-01-12 15:37:22.357762+00	71b06281-f5cd-4fa9-96a7-c8c9a76c01ec	\N	2022-06-07-today-i-went-shore-diving-in	Today I went shore diving in the lagoon and was able to take my tim...	published	public	[]	[]	Today I went shore diving in the lagoon and was able to take my tim...	Today I went shore diving in the lagoon and was able to take my time exploring a small part taking in the details and practicing underwater photography...			index, follow	{"meta": {"path": "/2022-06-07-today-i-went-shore-diving-in/", "slug": "2022-06-07-today-i-went-shore-diving-in", "title": "Today I went shore diving in the lagoon and was able to take my tim...", "robots": "index, follow", "seo_title": "Today I went shore diving in the lagoon and was able to take my tim...", "og_image_url": "", "seo_description": "Today I went shore diving in the lagoon and was able to take my time exploring a small part taking in the details and practicing underwater photography..."}, "blocks": [{"id": "b3463af0-a788-44b2-abf7-2443f20fe964", "data": {"content": "<p>Today I went shore diving in the lagoon and was able to take my time exploring a small part taking in the details and practicing underwater photography buoyancy and trim skills. I really enjoyed being patient and still in the warm water of the Caribbean, with no rush to swim around.  This gave the sea creatures time to get used to my bubbles.</p><p>At a depth of 5-6 meters my gas consumption was 1000psi every 30 or more minutes.  My dive plan was for 60 minutes.  I notified the park of my plan and went diving.  I did forgot my compass that needs to be replaced it's jacked up.  But I was still able to use the natural navigation details like the current, the angle of the sun (that changes), the ripples in the sand, the surge, and which features of coral and where certain schools of fish tend to live, the temperature, fresh water cenote vents, etc... to find my way back to exactly where on the beach I left my towel and shoes.</p><p>A huevo!</p><p>In July I am going to try to take the Guide course offered by the park.  It's all in Spanish.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 0}], "version": 1, "checksum": "6c06198a3ff9d46f33a796faadd75afb0d3a3315f1ef07eafdb57ac9ef2c0dc7", "published_at": "2026-01-12T15:31:01.857841+00:00", "access_control": {"level": "public", "required_roles": [], "required_entitlements": []}, "published_by_id": "1"}	2026-01-12 15:31:01.857841+00	0	t	default	{"source": "facebook", "original_date": "2022-06-07"}	1	70c922aa-9fcb-4b5e-8736-e82206cf5c37	Today I went shore diving in the lagoon and was able to take my time exploring a small part taking in the details and practicing underwater photography buoyancy and trim skills. I really enjoyed...	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/484284307_1030617379085125_5043373570538207710_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_s590x590_tt6&_nc_cat=109&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=127cfc&_nc_ohc=xaXcp3Dt5I4Q7kNvwHlphE8&_nc_oc=AdnEcIbY2vNoJttM_vUxK1UWFcsmpzbaeYh0jIYUSOWl0E6UDJYeKHRRL7M2btvlKlE&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fcun1-1.fna&_nc_gid=RDzH_9Oa7TIdauNqcmCV8Q&oh=00_Afp0vH9pRSmGw-kO4P2IsNGA_-XveBVKHm9hwvr2S4e8ig&oe=696AC890	post	1	["facebook-import", "buceo-feliz"]	1ebb6e5c-53b0-41b9-b643-fb7823358e35
2026-01-12 15:31:00.249519+00	2026-01-12 15:37:22.68965+00	01f4b95e-c450-49cc-a419-a0f5c5d76647	\N	2024-10-02-staying-streamlined-why-a-backup-mask	Staying Streamlined: Why a Backup Mask, Cutting Tool, and Spool/DSM...	published	public	[]	[]	Staying Streamlined: Why a Backup Mask, Cutting Tool, and Spool/DSM...	Staying Streamlined: Why a Backup Mask, Cutting Tool, and Spool/DSMB in a Butt Pouch Make Sense When it comes to diving, especially in technical...			index, follow	{"meta": {"path": "/2024-10-02-staying-streamlined-why-a-backup-mask/", "slug": "2024-10-02-staying-streamlined-why-a-backup-mask", "title": "Staying Streamlined: Why a Backup Mask, Cutting Tool, and Spool/DSM...", "robots": "index, follow", "seo_title": "Staying Streamlined: Why a Backup Mask, Cutting Tool, and Spool/DSM...", "og_image_url": "", "seo_description": "Staying Streamlined: Why a Backup Mask, Cutting Tool, and Spool/DSMB in a Butt Pouch Make Sense When it comes to diving, especially in technical..."}, "blocks": [{"id": "cc0068a5-cb09-440f-9584-fd4ad79d1fcf", "data": {"content": "<p>Staying Streamlined: Why a Backup Mask, Cutting Tool, and Spool/DSMB in a Butt Pouch Make Sense</p><p>When it comes to diving, especially in technical environments, staying streamlined is key. Whether you're navigating tight spaces or just trying to reduce drag, every piece of gear needs to have its place. One of the most practical solutions for staying streamlined while keeping essential gear accessible is using a butt pouch. In my case, I picked up an XDeep butt pouch during my cave diving course, and it's been a game-changer. Let me tell you why you should consider adding one to your kit.</p><p>A butt pouch allows you to carry critical backup gear\\\\u2014like a mask, cutting tool, and spool/DSMB\\\\u2014without cluttering the front of your setup. It sits snugly against your backplate, so you don\\\\u2019t feel it during the dive, and it\\\\u2019s easy to access when needed. I\\\\u2019ve added some bungee rings to the backplate to clip onto while diving backmount BPW (Backplate and Wing), and the whole setup stays clean and streamlined.</p><p>One of the benefits of a butt pouch is its simplicity. You don\\\\u2019t have to mess around with bulky side pockets or worry about stuff flapping around during your dive. Everything stays neatly packed away until you need it. This is especially useful for technical diving, where minimal drag and easy access to tools can be the difference between a smooth dive and a frustrating one.</p><p>However, if you\\\\u2019re like me and don\\\\u2019t want to spend a fortune on a brand-name pouch, you can go the DIY route. After buying an expensive one for my course, I ended up picking up some aftermarket pockets for cheap. With a little creativity, I rigged one to function as a butt pouch, and it works just as well as the high-end models. It\\\\u2019s an easy way to save money while keeping your setup streamlined.</p><p>Here's a video where I break down how I set up my butt pouch and show you how to do it yourself. Trust me, once you\\\\u2019ve got one in your kit, you won\\\\u2019t go back. It\\\\u2019s one of those things that makes every dive more efficient, safe, and organized.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 0}], "version": 1, "checksum": "0591148d291963648ca14534faba1dca165c2302f1c2dff15d6cd752c31611a6", "published_at": "2026-01-12T15:31:00.255889+00:00", "access_control": {"level": "public", "required_roles": [], "required_entitlements": []}, "published_by_id": "1"}	2026-01-12 15:31:00.255889+00	0	t	default	{"source": "facebook", "original_date": "2024-10-02"}	1	70c922aa-9fcb-4b5e-8736-e82206cf5c37	Staying Streamlined: Why a Backup Mask, Cutting Tool, and Spool/DSMB in a Butt Pouch Make Sense When it comes to diving, especially in technical environments, staying streamlined is key. Whether...	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/470148900_905918918191747_4362903535941773149_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_s590x590_tt6&_n