n the cenote today The buoyancy is a little different with sidemount. My homework is to dive...	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/484779819_1035300455283484_88497993461254441_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_p180x540_tt6&_nc_cat=105&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=127cfc&_nc_ohc=KPSx_YwQ9S4Q7kNvwGQw1-o&_nc_oc=AdlImXIZGkIW0TEXtvkiI48tcb9BqoWfzf5vucMl8ddG0jB6KRecgP3Ge-x0L9cc5oI&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fcun1-1.fna&_nc_gid=8-gxXrfduXbYjviJyjHFhw&oh=00_AfqO0UQj--ROPffDmVmg4I6DPSphlzHCe8J2SDFQpq_slQ&oe=696AE1C7	post	1	["facebook-import", "buceo-feliz"]	1ebb6e5c-53b0-41b9-b643-fb7823358e35
2026-01-12 15:31:01.579975+00	2026-01-12 15:37:22.412655+00	a631cd0f-34c8-40b3-b2a0-989c74f8ec38	\N	2022-09-15-ive-added-some-task-loading-today	I've added some task loading today during my sidemount training by ...	published	public	[]	[]	I've added some task loading today during my sidemount training by ...	I've added some task loading today during my sidemount training by bringing my Olympus TG-6 along.  I am able to stow the long-hose now a little...			index, follow	{"meta": {"path": "/2022-09-15-ive-added-some-task-loading-today/", "slug": "2022-09-15-ive-added-some-task-loading-today", "title": "I've added some task loading today during my sidemount training by ...", "robots": "index, follow", "seo_title": "I've added some task loading today during my sidemount training by ...", "og_image_url": "", "seo_description": "I've added some task loading today during my sidemount training by bringing my Olympus TG-6 along.  I am able to stow the long-hose now a little..."}, "blocks": [{"id": "acc044b7-4650-45eb-9668-b7644f794dba", "data": {"content": "<p>I've added some task loading today during my sidemount training by bringing my Olympus TG-6 along.</p><p>I am able to stow the long-hose now a little easier, even with one hand, so to give my mind some new focus points I brought the camera to shoot some photos of critters while also maintaining my good buoyancy and trim.</p><p>I removed the strobe and the wide angle lens to reduce the footprint of the camera and incrementally add more tasks with those items later in my training when I'm more automatic with muscle memory for managing the other skills.</p><p>I think challenges for me are a good way to learn and keep my interest but are best added incrementally in order to avoid being overwhelmed with task loading.  Having some real-world fun on long practice dives sure makes the skills homework more enjoyable.</p><p>I don't usually recommend divers add in a camera until after their skills are solid, they are familiar with the dive site, and .</p><p>I feel pretty solid with diving with 2 tanks now.  The fine motor skills and muscle memory for stowing things and getting them out, maintaining situational awareness while focusing on getting a good shot. All the while practicing good buoyancy is something I'm getting the hang of.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 0}], "version": 1, "checksum": "6b01fddcad7b9f1d90b91db763a97206ffac37eab9a5a3ad9a2286a467a1a1b7", "published_at": "2026-01-12T15:31:01.584886+00:00", "access_control": {"level": "public", "required_roles": [], "required_entitlements": []}, "published_by_id": "1"}	2026-01-12 15:31:01.584886+00	0	t	default	{"source": "facebook", "original_date": "2022-09-15"}	1	70c922aa-9fcb-4b5e-8736-e82206cf5c37	I've added some task loading today during my sidemount training by bringing my Olympus TG-6 along.  I am able to stow the long-hose now a little easier, even with one hand, so to give my mind some...	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/487508222_1045816674231862_8468867340695594948_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_s590x590_tt6&_nc_cat=101&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=833d8c&_nc_ohc=LlIdqEs3C9AQ7kNvwHKynH1&_nc_oc=AdkrobzBfWnVLta3hzryVsRgo7p9ZKukKQBFYVwUlQTL5GUmoHyPQsKwXYP0RvNNGWM&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fcun1-1.fna&_nc_gid=PPaK5iVvGRNo7tnjgBW84g&oh=00_AfqofB0asqC_qTM2-es90kxbv9ufNW55OxBjMZ102rrEjg&oe=696AF439	post	1	["facebook-import", "buceo-feliz"]	1ebb6e5c-53b0-41b9-b643-fb7823358e35
