los alimentos.</p><p>A pesar de lo inofensivos que pueden parecer los tiburones nodriza, ocupan el cuarto lugar en las mordeduras documentadas de tiburones en humanos, probablemente debido al comportamiento imprudente de los buzos debido a la naturaleza lenta y sedentaria del tibur\\\\u00f3n nodriza.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 0}], "version": 1, "checksum": "74963e7e80108793fa9185173d830afb9bb5d4e489a962013744d07921a3a385", "published_at": "2026-01-12T15:31:01.307560+00:00", "access_control": {"level": "public", "required_roles": [], "required_entitlements": []}, "published_by_id": "1"}	2026-01-12 15:31:01.30756+00	0	t	default	{"source": "facebook", "original_date": "2022-12-12"}	1	70c922aa-9fcb-4b5e-8736-e82206cf5c37	Nurse shark we found on our 2nd dive today.  Nurse sharks are obligate suction feeders capable of generating suction forces that are among the highest recorded for any aquatic vertebrate to date....	https://scontent.fcun1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/469012600_900739115376394_6997451709526273557_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_s590x590_tt6&_nc_cat=102&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=127cfc&_nc_ohc=rZT47YV6HToQ7kNvwGQSfTM&_nc_oc=AdnEU-hO9oWWMHZ09CufAPwKwuWYAHJQoVvtLrhE8_M5S4DB0sAVLEdpF0wR6h8Cg3Y&_nc_zt=23&_nc_ht=scontent.fcun1-1.fna&_nc_gid=4z8cnzxvsuD9VjpFIOAy-g&oh=00_AfosMwNW4864cBvqBQu-R8DhrhHrvQzbVsqkiXic-_NO8A&oe=696AD4F4	post	1	["facebook-import", "buceo-feliz"]	99de6173-8156-47ad-b4fa-e64b01814a44
2026-01-12 15:31:01.2871+00	2026-01-12 15:37:22.494637+00	806a9849-e6ed-4d3e-ab3b-e4039750bd6f	\N	2022-12-21-during-every-dive-managing-and-monitoring	During every dive, managing and monitoring your air by keeping an e...	published	public	[]	[]	During every dive, managing and monitoring your air by keeping an e...	During every dive, managing and monitoring your air by keeping an eye on your gauge regularly is one of the best things you can do to stay safe.  Here...			index, follow	{"meta": {"path": "/2022-12-21-during-every-dive-managing-and-monitoring/", "slug": "2022-12-21-during-every-dive-managing-and-monitoring", "title": "During every dive, managing and monitoring your air by keeping an e...", "robots": "index, follow", "seo_title": "During every dive, managing and monitoring your air by keeping an e...", "og_image_url": "", "seo_description": "During every dive, managing and monitoring your air by keeping an eye on your gauge regularly is one of the best things you can do to stay safe.  Here..."}, "blocks": [{"id": "e4a6c760-250a-45d2-80e9-a5050dfb8d1b", "data": {"content": "<p>During every dive, managing and monitoring your air by keeping an eye on your gauge regularly is one of the best things you can do to stay safe.</p><p>Here are a few tips:\\n\\\\ud83d\\\\udca8 Verify air is turned on right before jumping in the water. Make sure to do this by taking a few complete breaths and watching your gauge/watch for any changes.</p><p>\\\\u2b07\\\\ufe0f Ensure you have enough air for your dive (i.e., leave enough air for the return, 1/2 or 1/3 rule).</p><p>\\\\ud83d\\\\udc40 While diving, check your gauge/watch regularly and stay close to your buddy.</p><p>\\\\u270b\\\\ud83c\\\\udffd Make a complete stop (safety or decompression) with at least 500 psi/50 bar remaining.</p><p>What other tips would you add to this list?</p><p>#diversalertnetwork #dan #scuba #scubadiving #scubadiver #scubatrips #underwater #ocean #air #tips #gauge #vacation #bubbles</p>"}, "type": "r